he color stays put morning-to-night for worry-free brows.", "This brow gel works due to its careful marriage of formula and brush. The fragrance-free formula clings to existing brow hairs and helps set them in place without looking stiff.  The advantage of such a slim spoolie is that you can really target where you want to emphasize your brows (hello arches!). What if you have sparse brows? Angle the tip of the spoolie to subtly fill in those areas.", "Shade-wise, you can pick from Taupe, Medium Brown and Black Brown. We're hoping Tarte expands that to include even more options in the future because we really like this product and would love to see options for all brow colors!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 14}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/nourishing-brow-pencil/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyebrow-pencil-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyebrow-pencil-reviews ", "product_names": "Nourishing Brow Pencil", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyebrow Makeup", "brand": "Neutrogena", "ingredient": "Dimethicone,  Synthetic wax,  Octyldodecanol,  Polybutene,  Cetearyl Behenate,  Disteardimonium Hectorite,  Sorbitan Olivate,  Propylene Carbonate,  Synthetic Fluorphlogopite,  Synthetic Beeswax,  Pentaerythrityl Tetra-di-t-butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate. May contain: Iron Oxides,  Titanium Dioxide,  Mica", "size": "0.04 fl. oz.", "price": "9.99", "claims": "Define and shape your eyebrows in one step. This 2-in-1 brow pencil with a spoolie brush creates a natural-looking matte finish.", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/BD4357F9-4B65-4725-A4CC-4439BDC33D80_neutrogenanourishingbrowpencil.jpg?w=522", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["Nourishing Brow Pencil is an OK option for filling in brows, but there's not much to get excited about here, compared to the superior (and in some cases, less expensive) brow enhancers at the drugstore!", "This is a standard, manual-sharpening-required brow pencil, with an attached spoolie brush on the opposite end. The pencil's texture is creamy enough to glide on smoothly, but overall it lacks the precision that better brow pencils offer.", "The color payoff is good, with a few shades for brunettes and one for blondes. The staying power is adequate once set.", "The bottom line: Nourishing Brow Pencil isn't bad per se, but we think you could do better. Take a peek at our Best Eyebrow Fillers list."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 15}
