{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/fluidline-brow-gelcreme/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyebrow-pencil-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyebrow-pencil-reviews ", "product_names": "Fluidline Brow GelCreme", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyebrow Makeup", "brand": "M.A.C.", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "17.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/F00255B1-826C-4F43-A571-506045932168_m.a.c_fluidline_brow_gelcreme.jpg?w=1024", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["Fluidline Brow GelCreme can take a little bit of practice to master, but once you have the knack, it creates full, sculpted brows for a more defined look. Because the solid-cream formula is housed in a clear pot, you'll need some sort of brush to apply it with. M.A.C. sells several, but you can use your own (an angled brush works well).", "To apply you simply dab your brush in the cream and blend into brows. How bold depends on your technique, but ultimately brows are left looking more dense, groomed, and structured. If desired, you can extend to the outer edges of your natural brow line with swift, thin strokes.", "The fragrance-free formula allows ample time before setting, which is a good thing so you can perfect the shape. Once set, the color stays in place and holds up well against water as claimed. The formula also helps set brow hairs in place for an overall groomed look, yet still leaves them pliable so they don't appear matted down.", "There are three shades available: Dirty Blonde, Redhead, and Deep Dark Brunette, each of which delivers believable brow color true to their shade names.", "This isn't the fastest way to color and sculpt brows, but with a little patience, the results are impressive. Kudos, M.A.C.!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 59}
