{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/double-wear-stay-in-place-brow-lift-duo/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyebrow-pencil-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyebrow-pencil-reviews ", "product_names": "Double Wear Stay-in-Place Brow Lift Duo", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyebrow Makeup", "brand": "Estee Lauder", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "26.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/A45221CC-16D4-44B3-8C41-FC868178D49F_21ufJDyxuDL.jpg?w=326", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["This slim, automatic, retractable brow pencil comes in a great range of shades for blonde to dark brown brows, and its opposite end has a twist-up, retractable cream highlighter pencil for creating a lifted look at the high point of the eyebrow's arch.", "The effect of the highlighter pencil is subtle, but noticeable, and it's the same soft, golden peach color with a hint of shine for each shade of the brow pencil. Granted, you could achieve the same thing with strategically applied powder eyeshadow or highlighter, but having it built in is a convenience that somewhat offsets the slightly higher cost.", "The brow pencil itself goes on easily, but don't press too hard or the tip will break. Once you get the hang of it, you'll see it's not a formulary flaw but an asset: Few brow pencils in recent memory go on this smoothly and also last. The pencil's powder-like finish stays in place for hours, although you may notice slight fading by the end of the day, and certainly will if you habitually rub your brows.", "All of the shades are recommended, but there are no viable options for redheads or those with auburn brows, whether natural or dyed."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 62}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/dipbrow-pomade/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyebrow-pencil-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyebrow-pencil-reviews ", "product_names": "Dipbrow Pomade", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyebrow Makeup", "brand": "Anastasia of Beverly Hills", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "18.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/37B79215-75FC-40FF-B855-C3E2C4D77989_Anastasia_DipbrowPomade.jpg?w=300", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["If there's one thing Anastasia Beverly Hills knows, it's brow makeup\u2013 and it has another winner on its hands with Dipbrow Pomade.", "This cream/gel hybrid comes in a glass jar with a screw top lid. It isn't waxy or hard at all \u2013 it has a consistency that's quite soft and easy to pick up on your brow brush of choice. It takes little effort to apply, and you only need a very small amount to get good color deposit (we found one dip of our brush into the pomade was enough to provide color for both brows, with product to spare).", "Dipbrow wears well throughout the day without fading or smudging, and keeps brows soft (and more natural-looking) during its impressive wear time. It comes in a good range of shades for blonde, auburn, and dark brows \u2013 with the darker shades being able to do double duty as gel eyeliner (though if you opt to use this product as eyeliner, make sure you use a different brush than you did for the brows)."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 63}
