{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/pur-ly-abundant-lash-brow-duo-wand/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Flash-treatment-and-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Dlash-treatment-and-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Pur-ly Abundant Lash & Brow Duo Wand", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyelash Primer & Treatment", "brand": "P\u00fcrminerals", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "26.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/8C240744-DE2F-4CD4-99FD-860D3F8AA1A0_Pur-Minerals_logo.jpg?w=400", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["This dual-sided product includes a tinted brow \u201cprimer\u201d on one end and a clear \u201ctreatment\u201d on the other. Both sides are said to stimulate growth of eyebrow and eyelash hair follicles, resulting in abundant brows and lashes. The primer portion contains nothing that\u2019s not found in numerous other tinted brow gels, and its sheer color works minimally to enhance brows. The treatment portion is mostly water, slip agents, film-forming agents, and familiar plant extracts. It does contain one ingredient worth further discussion because there is a limited amount of research pertaining to its potential to promote hair growth. Apigenin is a flavonoid present in many fruits, vegetables, and teas. Animal studies have shown it stimulates hair growth by downregulating a key gene that influences the catagen (resting) phase of hair growth. By blunting the influence of this gene, hair stays in the anagen (growth) phase longer (Source: Archives of Dermatological Research, June 2009, pages 381\u2013385). What isn\u2019t known is how this ingredient works on human hair (be it on the scalp or along the lash line) and how much is needed to promote growth or even if it\u2019s safe. Needless to say, one animal study isn\u2019t much to go on, though the theory is intriguing. I wouldn\u2019t bank on this product promoting eyebrow or eyelash growth, but you could certainly give it a try and see what happens\u2014it\u2019s not nearly as expensive as lots of other brow and lash growth products being sold. If nothing else, the clear treatment product doubles as a decent brow gel!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 217}
