r liner does, too!", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/29CAB787-536C-4F8E-A45D-BD1A46021A20_itcosmeticssuperheroliner.jpg?w=437", "expert_rating": "1", "expert_reviews": ["Superhero Liner initially goes on beautifully, but its downfall (or Kryptonite, if you prefer) is that it's prone to transferring throughout the day.", "At first, all seemed well and good\u2014we love the way this liquid liner's fine-tip, synthetic hair brush makes application so precise, gliding on with perfect fluidity for super-smooth, solid color.", "The trouble starts a few hours later, at which point color begins transferring to the upper eye area. We tried alleviating this issue by applying our favorite eyeshadow primer first, but not even that could help. After several days of various testing methods, we were defeated\u2014overcoming Superhero Liner's transferring issue was more trouble than it's worth.", "We're also concerned about the high concentration of alcohol, which is a known skin irritant. Essentially that outweighs any benefit that you could theoretically get from the other ingredients that It Cosmetics is touting in this fragrance-free formula.", "What a letdown, especially for the price. See our top-rated eyeliners instead."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 233}
