{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/infinite-liquid-eye-liner/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeliner-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeliner-reviews%26p%3D2 ", "product_names": "Infinite Liquid Eye Liner", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeliner", "brand": "Milani", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "6.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/2C37F8E5-678A-4A47-9722-58FDAFC4EF2C_41NqzbBbOyL.jpg?w=202", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["Milani touts Infinite Liquid Eye Liner as able to last up to 24 hours. That\u2019s really not too far of stretch because the formula is very tenacious, and you can count on smudge-free, flake-free wear throughout the day. (You\u2019ll definitely want eye makeup remover to get it off.) However, unless you plan to forgo sleep, keeping any eyeliner on for 24 hours isn\u2019t a good idea; going to bed with eye makeup on is a surefire way to wake up to puffy, red, irritated eyes!", "The wet application takes a while to dry down so you have to be patient, but it pays off with dramatic bold color in classic shades like black or brown, as well as trendier shades like blue, green, and purple.", "The liquid formula goes on smooth with a flexible brush that allows you to create a thick or thin line, depending on your preference. All told, this is a long-lasting eyeliner option at a bargain price!", "Pros:", "Cons:"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 331}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-booster-2-in-1-lash-boosting-felt-tip-eyeliner-serum/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeliner-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeliner-reviews%26p%3D2 ", "product_names": "Eye Booster 2-in-1 Lash Boosting Felt-Tip Eyeliner + Serum", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeliner", "brand": "Physicians Formula", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "10.95", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/AED98343-0433-4F38-8D57-23676C816501_PhysiciansFormulaEyeBoosterFeltTip.jpg?w=1000", "expert_rating": "1", "expert_reviews": ["A word of caution: You may think the liquid eyeliner portion of this product is identical to Physician\u2019s Formula\u2019s Eye Booster 2-in-1 Lash Boosting Eyeliner + Serum (a BEST product), but it\u2019s not the same product. Other than the similar name, the only thing these two eyeliners have in common is that there\u2019s no published research showing the ingredients in either product are going to help grow even a single eyelash.", "That said, the Felt-Tip Eyeliner included with this product is stoutly shaped and excels at drawing a thick line over lids\u2014think of a black Sharpie pen. Physician\u2019s Formula labels this eyeliner with a twenty-four hour wear claim, but that\u2019s a stretch if we\u2019ve ever heard one. Humidity? Oily eyelids? Forget about it. Despite looking like a permanent marker, Felt-Tip eyeliner pen is anything but long-wearing or water-resistant. In fact, the major deal-breaker with this eyeliner is its inability to stay in place. We\u2019d love this thick, matte, liner in all four colors if it didn\u2019t bleed into creases and smudge around eyes, but that\u2019s too many negatives for anyone to have to put up with.", "Pros:", "Cons:"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 332}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/smoldereyes-amazonian-clay-waterproof-eye-liner/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeliner-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeliner-reviews%26p%3D2 ", "product_names": "SmolderEYES Amazonian Clay Waterproof Eye Liner", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeliner", "brand": "Tarte Cosmetics", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "22.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/B0A16141-67F6-4FB4-86C8-126C04142067_TarteSmolderEyesLiner.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": [" This chubby, needs-sharpening, eyeliner pencil draws on a thick water-resistant line that can be easily softened (if desired) by the built-in rubber smudger on the bottom of the pencil. SmolderEYES can be worn alone, or set with a powder eyeshadow for extra durability. The colors range from neutral browns and charcoal to violet and indigo, most of which have gold-toned specks of glitter. Thankfully, the glitter stays on and does not flake into eyes\u2014though, we do not recommend using this (or any) liner to rim the waterline of the eye.", " Claims regarding \"micronized clay\" from the Amazon River are marketing hype. Clay\u2014no matter where it's from\u2014won't have an effect on how well eyeliner lasts, although clay can help absorb excess oil and too much clay in an eyeliner formula can create a dry texture that drags along skin as you apply.", " All things considered, the only thing eye-popping about this ho-hum eyeliner is the price tag. For better options (many less expensive, that don't require sharpening), see our list of Best Eyeliners.", " Pros:", " Cons:"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 333}
