  Zinc Stearate,  Squalane,  Silica,  Dimethicone,  Lauroyl Lysine,  Hydrogenated Lecithin,  Trimyristin,  Caprylyl Glycol,  Hexylene Glycol,  Phenoxyethanol. May Contain (+/-): Titaium Dioxide,  Iron Oxides,  Ultramarines.", "size": "5.00 grams", "price": "58.00", "claims": "An artist-inspired eye shadow palette with seamless color transitionsoffering effortlessly blendable and wearable shades in a range of finishes and textures.", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/15C2EDFF-C07C-475B-9653-0420D0F29CF2_HourglassModernistEyeshadowPalette.jpg?w=1024", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Hourglass certainly knows what it's doing when it comes to product packaging! The Modernist series of palettes is gorgeous: Each contains five powder shadow colors arranged in a wave-like pattern that looks like sand art in a sleek, attractive compact. But does a pretty palette equal pretty performance? Unfortunately in this case, the answer is no!", "The main issue is the sparkly metallic shade included in almost every palette (save for the Atmosphere palette, whose shades are a mix of matte and satin matte finishes). Whether or not sparkle is your goal, no one wants a poorly performing shadow\u2014the Modernist's sparkle formula flakes throughout the day, leaving you with noticeable flecks of shadow on the tops of your cheekbones and under your eyes by the time you're ready to remove your makeup.", "Hourglass is correct when it says these shadows are incredibly soft. They have a buttery, almost cream-like texture that's easy to pick up on your brush, and the color quality is strong. But blendability is a problem with all of these shadows regardless of their finish.", "The blending issue is particularly true of the darker shades in each palette, which tend to cling unevenly to the areas where you apply them, leading to a blotchy look. You can blend them with a light, fluffy brush, but it takes some work! Once blended, these shadows last about seven hours without fading.", "All the palettes feature mostly neutral colors and attractive shade combinations. For all the hype though, this is just an average product due to the issues with blending and flaking. You'll find much better options (both in single and palette form) on our list of Best Eyeshadows.", "Check out the video review", "Pros:", "Cons:"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 623}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-tint/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Eye Tint", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Giorgio Armani", "ingredient": "Water,  Propylene Glycol,  Talc,  Synthetic Fluorphlogopite,  Lauroyl Lysine,  Octyldodecyl Stearoyl Stearate Dimethicone,  Boron Nitride,  Zea Mays Starch,  Dipentaerythrityl Tetrahydroxystearate,  Calcium Sodium Borosilicate,  Dimethicone/Vinyl Dimethicone Crosspolymer,  Sorbitan,  Isotearate Phenoxyethanol,  Stearath-20,  Argilla/Magnesium Aluminum Silicate Magnesium Silicate,  PEG-75 Stearate,  Silica,  Calcium Aluminum Borosilicate,  Silica[Nano}/Silica, Xanthan Gum,  Tin Oxide,  Caprylyl Glycol,  Acrylates Copolymer,  Cetyl Alcohol,  Ceteth-20,  Alumina,  Glycerin,  Glyceryl Stearate,  May Contain CI 77891/Titanium Dioxide,  CI 77491,  CI 77492,  CI 77499/Iron Oxides,  CI 77007/Ultramarines,  CI77400/Bronze Powder,  CI77400 Copper Powder,  CI77288/Chromium Oxide Greens,  CI 75470/Carmine,  CI 77163 Bismuth Oxychloride,  CI 77510/ Ferric Ferrocyanide,  CI 77742/ Manganese Violet,  CI77120/Barium Sulfate,  CI19140/Yellow 5 Lake,  CI42090/ Blue 1 Lake,  Mica.", "size": "0.22 fl. oz.", "price": "38.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/6CE9E9D0-201D-4661-ADA6-32F50B818853_giorgioarmani.jpg?w=180", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Armani claims this liquid eyeshadow in a tube is a first-of-its-kind product, which sounds pretty impressive. While that is not actually the case (there are other brands who've come out with similar shadows, so Armani isn't reinventing the wheel here), this is a good shadow option, but with one caveat.", "Like many Armani makeup products, the packaging is sleek and features a silver cap with an attached wand. Application is easy; just swipe the wand across your lids to deposit color. You can use either your fingers or a brush to blend, and\u2014good news\u2014there is time to blend (about a minute or so) before this formula sets to a powder finish.", "Once the formula sets, it stays put, with no creasing or fading throughout the day. It also feels incredibly smooth and doesn't weigh down lids, which some heavier cream shadows can do. Though Armani's advertising highlights the more colorful shades (such as a dark blue shade and a couple of green shades), there are neutral offerings to create a more subtle look if you choose. All the shades have shimmer, but they aren't sparkly\u2014and the shimmer doesn't flake.", "The only drawback is that you need to mix the formula a bit in the tube to make sure you get a consistent application every time. Most of the time when you pull out the wand you will get full color, but there are occasions when the formula settles, which can make it watery and sheer. It's a quick fix, but one to keep in mind.", "Overall, this is a great (albeit pricey) shadow, especially for application on the go!  For a better visual, check out our video review of Eye Tint on the Beautypedia YouTube channel!", "Pros:", "Cons:"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 624}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/photoready-eye-art-lid-line-lash/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "PhotoReady Eye Art Lid + Line + Lash", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Revlon", "ingredient": null, "size": "0.10 fl. oz.", "price": "7.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/9C1F9EDC-F55F-48B6-84E1-628F4F5E4A68_RevlonPhotoReadyEyeArtLidLineLash.jpg?w=160", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["PhotoReady Eye Art comes as an eye-catching shadow duo in a sparkling array of colorful shades. The dual-ended applicator features a shimmering, ultra-shiny cream shadow on one end and a complementary glittery overlay on the other. The combined effect is a standout eye design that could be fun for a night out on the town or other special occasions.", "In terms of application, a little goes a long way with the solid cream shadow; just a dab with the sponge-tip applicator will do it, and make sure to blend quickly because this sets fast! Although the fluid cream formula spreads smoothly over skin, it's tricky to get soft, rounded edges with a consistency like this. (It can be done, but it takes adept blending.) Once set, the shadow holds up impressively throughout the day, without creasing, flaking, or fading!", "As for the glittery accompaniment, it has more of a gel-like, wet formula that takes a bit longer to set. The brush it's applied with resembles a thin nail-polish brush, and it works OK. Revlon's ads showcase this as an eyeliner, but we think of it more as a topcoat because most of the shades go on as a sheer layer of sparkle. Once set, you can count on worry-free wear\u2014no glittery fallout here!", "Revlon also states that you can paint this product on lashes for extra pizzazz. We tried it that way and it looked costume-y, but go for it if you want!", "Calling this Eye Art is apropos given the rainbow of color options and the almost arts-and-craftsy appearance. This certainly isn't for the color- or sparkle-shy, but if you're intrigued by the long-lasting wear and dazzling effect, then by all means, give it a go!", "Of all the shades, the bronze-based Topaz Twinkle is the most universally wearable. This product is fragrance-free.", "Pros:", "Cons:"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 625}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/ombre-matte-eyeshadow-cream-to-powder-smoothing-long-lasting/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Ombre Matte Eyeshadow Cream-To-Powder Smoothing & Long-Lasting", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Clarins", "ingredient": null, "size": "7.00 grams", "price": "24.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/04788F34-072B-4F1A-9A56-BE978C2F27F7_ClarinsOmbreMatteCreamToPowderEyeshadow.jpg?w=160", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["This eyeshadow from Clarins has a long-winded name that's not entirely accurate. The texture feels more like a cushiony powder than a cream, but it glides on smoothly and blends softly into skin. You can apply this fragrance-free formula with your fingertips or a brush; either way, you'll experience minimal flaking or fallout.", "As for durability, these are touted as providing long-lasting, worry-free wear, and for the most part that's true. Those with oily eyelids will still notice creasing a few hours in, but otherwise, the color holds up reasonably without much fading by day's end.", "Speaking of color, these shadows come in a handful of satin-matte shades, except for Sparkle Grey, which has a shinier, iridescent finish. Nude Beige and Nude Pink are on the lighter side; the rest of the shades range from taupe to brown. The colors tend to go on softly, but if you're looking for stronger color payoff, try Sparkle Grey or Earth.", "All things considered, this a good cream-to-powder eyeshadow, but nothing to get overly excited about. The plastic jar container and gold lid are pretty to look at; just make sure to tightly close the lid each time so the shadow maintains its texture.", "Pros:", "Cons:"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 626}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/les-4-ombres-multi-effect-quadra-eyeshadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Les 4 Ombres Multi-Effect Quadra Eyeshadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Chanel", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "61.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/D20FA2FE-6617-477F-98EF-756220E71EF8_chanellogo.gif?w=112", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["A Chanel staple for years, Les 4 Ombres De Chanel Quadra Eyeshadow has been revamped into an even glitzier version: Les 4 Ombres Multi-Effect Quadra Eyeshadow. Currently, both the new and original versions are being sold side by side, both online and in-store, which can get a little confusing because they aren't differentiated very well, unless you're in the know. To help clear up the confusion when you're shopping, the powder shadows in the new Multi-Effect version of Les 4 Ombres Eyeshadows are circular rather than the original's square shape.", "Note: The Chanel representatives we spoke with assured us that the original formula isn't going away (at least for now).", "Similar to its predecessor, Les 4 Ombres Multi-Effect Quadra Eyeshadow has an enviable silky, pressed-powder texture, although this time it feels almost creamy. Just like the original, these fragrance-free shadows blend on like butter, making even application a breeze. The difference is that these shades are even more intensely shiny, some bordering on '70s sequined glitterball shine; for the most part, you get more shine than you do color. On the upside, the glitter and shimmer cling well to the skin without noticeable flaking; however, we did notice that the color fades a bit as the day wears on.", "Each quad is designed around the concept of offering two medium-tone shades, a deep shadow to intensify and a light shade to highlight. While there are certainly some attractive color combinations, we really wish there were at least one matte shade in each set. As is, those with crepey eyelids will notice that the shine exacerbates their wrinkly skin.", "In the end, if you're looking for a shimmery, sparkly, dazzling eyeshadow quad, Les 4 Ombres Multi-Effect Quadra Eyeshadow fits the bill. But if obvious shine isn't your thing or you don't want to draw attention to wrinkly eyelids, we recommend looking elsewhere."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 627}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-brow-maestro/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Eye & Brow Maestro", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Giorgio Armani", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "34.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/F091742A-4B50-4A05-80C5-C76D77EA0A9D_GiorgioArmaniEyeBrowMaestro.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Eye & Brow Maestro is touted as a multitasking wonder to fill brows, while also being capable of functioning as an eyeshadow or eyeliner. They even go so far as to say that it can be used for contouring the face and to cover roots or gray hair. We'll address those claims in a minute, but for now let's focus on how most people will use this product's solid-cream texture, which is for the eyes and brows.", "While we love a multitasking product just as much as the next person, this glass jar\u2013packaged product doesn't end up being as handy as it sounds. Case in point: The shade you use on your brows isn't necessarily the color you'll want to use as eyeshadow, and vice versa.", "There are a few shades that are passable as brow colors for blondes and brunettes, as well for black and gray hair. Each has at least a hint of shimmer, if not more. For the most part, the shimmer isn't all that noticeable in the brows, which is a good thing because sparkly brows aren't all that natural-looking. Using Eye & Brow Maestro to fill and shape the brows, it blends on smoothly between brow hairs and stays put decently well.", "The other shades in no way resemble natural brow colors and are obviously more geared toward use as an eyeshadow or eyeliner. There aren't very many of these other shades so not everyone will find a color they love; the bigger issue, however, is that they don't blend on that gracefully for a smooth eye design and can end up looking a little rough around the edges as a shadow. Some of the shades also go on much more sheer than you'd expect and they don't build color very well. As for the claims about this being waterproof: It's true that it does hold up well against water, but not against oily eyelids. If you're prone to creasing, you'll still likely experience that. In the brows it holds up better because your brow hairs help it stay in place.", "This doesn't come with an applicator/brush, but Armani of course sells one to accompany Eye & Brow Maestro, and although it works nicely (thin, slanted brush with a spoolie on the opposite end), you certainly can use a similar brush you already have at home or buy one for far less at the drugstore.", "Last, but not least: The fragrance-free formula doesn't blend on smoothly enough to contour your face, nor would you likely be able to find a shade that would look right for that. As for covering roots, the texture isn't the best for that, so Armani essentially really overexaggerates what this product can do. It's not the multitasking wonder it's claimed to be.", "Bottom line: We don't hate this product, but we certainly don't love it. For all it promises, it just doesn't deliver."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 628}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/intense-kohl-eye-crayon/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Intense Kohl Eye Crayon", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Dolce & Gabbana", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "30.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/9E2FF1CE-2818-4AE9-BBAF-9347177B1BE4_dolce-and-gabbana-official.jpg?w=229", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Intense Kohl Eye Crayon is a richly-pigmented, creamy-soft pencil that produces a smooth line of smudgeable color. We love how easy it is to blend out the fragrance-free formula for a smokey eye, but it's so movable that it tends to smear.", "This pencil also comes with the inconvenience of needing to be manually sharpened, a less desirable trait that wastes product, which at this price you probably don't want to do!", "If the price doesn't deter you, there are classic black and brown shades, as well as more colorful options with a metallic sheen. Either way, we wouldn't count on this for all-day wear, and at this price, you really should be able to apply it and forget about it!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 629}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/the-eyeshadow-smooth-eye-color-duo/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "The Eyeshadow Smooth Eye Color Duo", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Dolce & Gabbana", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "43.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/9E2FF1CE-2818-4AE9-BBAF-9347177B1BE4_dolce-and-gabbana-official.jpg?w=229", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["The Eyeshadow Smooth Eye Color Duo comes with two shades of pressed-powder eyeshadow in a variety of color combos and finishes. The level of pigmentation varies from shade to shade, but all are buildable and wear well throughout the day, without fading or flaking. We also appreciate how smoothly the silky-soft pressed-powder texture blends on, whether you're going for a natural or dramatic look.", "Not all of the color duos are complementary and flattering (purple and lime green, anyone?), but there are a few attractive sets that may strike your fancy. Some offer a matte shade, and most come with at least one noticeably shimmery color.", "While this fragrance-free eyeshadow performs adequately, and the decadent, golden Dolce & Gabbana case is pretty to behold, is it really worth paying this much? That's a subjective question, but keep in mind that no one can tell that you're wearing a \"designer brand\" eyeshadow once it's on\u2014overpaying doesn't make you look several dollars more chic."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 630}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/perfect-mono-intense-cream-eye-colour/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Perfect Mono Intense Cream Eye Colour", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Dolce & Gabbana", "ingredient": "Dimethicone,  Mica,  Isododecane,  Silica,  C30-45 Alkyl Dimethicone,  Dextrin Palmitate,  Vinyl Dimethicone/Ethicone Silsesquioxane Crosspolymer,  Acrylates Copolymer,  Zinc Stearate,  Methicone,  Talc,  Dimethicone Crosspolymer,  Ethylene/Methacrylate Copolymer,  Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate,  Tin Oxide,  Polyhydroxystearic Acid,  Isopropyl Titanium Triisostearate,  Phenoxyethanol,  [(+/-)/May Contain: CI 77891/Titanium Dioxide,  (CI 77491,  CI 77492,  CI 77499)/Iron Oxides,  CI 77007/Ultramarines,  CI 77163/Bismuth Oxychloride,  CI 42090/Blue 1 Lake,  CI 75470/Carmine,  CI 77510/Ferric Ferrocyanide]. NOTE: Ingredients may vary by shade from the above listing.", "size": "", "price": "37.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/9E2FF1CE-2818-4AE9-BBAF-9347177B1BE4_dolce-and-gabbana-official.jpg?w=229", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["Perfect Mono Intense Cream Eye Colour has a soft, bouncy, mousse-like, cream-to-powder texture that blends effortlessly into the skin. Whether applied with your fingertips or a brush (not included), you get fade-proof, crease-resistant color that lasts from day to night.", "The collection boasts a multitude of shimmering and matte-finish options, from iridescent pale pink to neutral brown all the way to black, plus several more playful colors in between. This beautiful cream-to-powder eyeshadow can be applied sheer or patted onto your eyelids or the underbrow area for more dramatic, bold color.", "We must applaud D&G for this one: Perfect Mono Intense Cream Eye Colour does not disappoint! Bonus: It's fragrance-free.", "Note: Be sure to close the screw-top packaging tightly after each use. Otherwise, the cream shadow will dry out prematurely, and at this price, that's a big waste of money!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 631}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/the-eyeshadow-smooth-eye-color-quad/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "The Eyeshadow Smooth Eye Color Quad", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Dolce & Gabbana", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "60.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/9E2FF1CE-2818-4AE9-BBAF-9347177B1BE4_dolce-and-gabbana-official.jpg?w=229", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["This fragrance-free powder eyeshadow quad offers a silky-soft texture that blends smoothly across the eye area and holds up well throughout the day without flaking or fading.", "The color combos are hit or miss, but there are some attractive options to explore. Opacity varies among the four shades in each set, but most of them consistently offer what's best described as a mid-level sheerness that can be layered for more intensity. There is also a contrast among the finish of the colors in each quad, ranging from matte to metallic or satin.", "Smooth Eye Color Quad beams with elegance from the outside with its decadent, golden Dolce & Gabbana case and performs adequately, but is it really worth paying this much? That's a subjective question, but keep in mind that no one can tell the difference once you've got it on\u2014overpaying doesn't make you look several dollars more chic.", "Given that you don't get any more product than with most eyeshadows, the price is hard to justify, especially considering there are plenty of other eyeshadow quads that perform equally or better for just a nibble of the price. Still, if the expense doesn't hold you back, this is a decent option."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 632}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/color-tattoo-leather-by-eyestudio-24hr-eyeshadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Color Tattoo Leather by Eyestudio 24HR Eyeshadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Maybelline New York", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "6.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/2D822236-E4E0-47AB-9F50-AAB5C2DE73EA_MaybellineLeatherTattoo.jpg?w=1019", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Color Tattoo Leather cream-to-powder eyeshadow is meant to resemble the look of \u201ccouture leather so right\u201d\u2026because how many times have you wished someone, somewhere would come out with a leather-like eyeshadow? The trendy look to wear intense eyeliner means you can now match it with equally intense tones such as \u00a0shades of brown, beige, olive, plum and black.\u00a0", "Housed in a screw-top jar, you can apply Color Tattoo Leather with your fingertips or a synthetic eyeshadow brush, and the fragrance-free formula allows ample time to blend before drying down to its budge-proof finish. No creasing or flaking here!", "Another use for this is as an eyeshadow primer. We found that layering powder shadow on top of Color Tattoo Leather helps it stay put and produces amazingly rich results.", "Speaking of shades, most in the Leather collection have a matte finish; the exception being Chocolate Suede which has a metallic shimmer. For whatever reason, that shade seemed a tad trickier to blend. \u00a0The other variance among shades is how deep or sheer they go on. For instance, Vintage Plum and Deep Forest take more layering to produce a solid color, whereas Dramatic Black is more intensely pigmented and goes on that way from the get-go.", "All in all, if you can find a shade you like Color Tattoo Leather is a beauty bargain to behold!", "Pros:", "Cons:"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 633}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/5-in-1-bb-cream-shadow-spf-15/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "5-in-1 BB Cream Shadow SPF 15", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Bare Minerals (Bare Escentuals)", "ingredient": "Active: Titanium Dioxide 17%: Sunscreen. Inactive: Isododecane,  Disteardimonium Hectorite,  Polymethylsilsesquioxane,  Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride,  Propylene Carbonate,  Silica,  Trimethylsiloxysilicate,  Dipalmitoyl Hydroxyproline,  Mangifera Indica (Mango) Seed Butter,  Carthamus Tinctorius (Safflower) Seed Oil,  Camellia Oleifera Leaf Extract,  Acrylates Copolymer,  Diacetyl Boldine,  Calcium Sodium Borosilicate,  Calcium Aluminum Borosilicate,  Tin Oxide,  Phenoxyethanol. May Contain: Mica,  Carmine,  Titanium Dioxide,  Iron Oxides,  Bismuth Oxychloride,  Chromium Hydroxide Green,  Chromium Oxide Greens,  Ferric Ferrocyanide,  Manganese Violet,  Ultramarines. NOTE: Ingredients may vary by shade from the above listing.", "size": "0.10 fl. oz.", "price": "19.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/09A50D5C-D083-4057-B45B-17AF9410A754_bare_escentuals_bare_minerals_5in1_bb_cream_shadow_spf15.jpg?w=497", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["Eyeshadow with built-in SPF is a rare commodity, and this one delivers it in a mineral-based, broad spectrum sun protection formula that is both fragrance-free and gentle for the eye area!", "We've been coming down a bit harder on products rated SPF 15 due to SPF ratings of 20 and above being the new normal around the world, mostly because people aren't applying such products liberally enough to get the stated amount of protection. However, we're giving this eyeshadow a pass because simply including some sunscreen is an advantage\u2014but don't forget those sunglasses, too!", "Sun protection is just one of the many benefits attributed to the \"5-in-1\" name. Long-wearing color, priming capabilities, brightening effects, and smoothed appearance of fine lines are the other four, and we're happy to report that this eyeshadow really does live up to each of those claims!", "5-in-1 BB Cream Shadow comes in a frosted glass tube outfitted with a sponge-tip applicator. A little goes a long way, whether you apply this with the included wand or just your fingertips. The lightweight, creamy texture goes on like a breeze and allows ample time to blend before it dries down to a matte (in feel) finish.", "This cream shadow serves dual-purpose as a primer for other powder shadows and it also prevents powder eyeshadows from flaking throughout the day. Even after several hours of wear we still didn't have creasing (and that's typically a real problem for some of us)!", "The lighter shades can also function as a brightener under your normal shadow. The understated sparkly finish adds a dash of radiance, but isn't blatant like many other glitter or shimmer shadows. It looks matte, but just with a finely milled overlay of sparkle (that you have to look closely to see).", "True to claim, 5-in-1 BB Cream Shadow does a good job of minimizing the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles\u2026 particularly if you select a darker shade (those camouflage wrinkly skin better than the lighter colors).", "The shade range consists of flattering neutrals including shades of brown, taupe, beige, and cream, as well as subdued hues of peach, pink, green and plum. Those who desire a more dramatic or trendy color palette may be disappointed, but we're guessing that if these eyeshadows are successful as we think they'll be, eventually more shades will be added. The pigmentation goes on opaque but sheers out as you blend. For more intensity you can pat it on or layer it without it looking cakey.", "The downside to any cream shadow is that if you're going for a multi-colored eye design they're a little trickier to work with than a normal powder eyeshadow, but nonetheless, 5-in-1 BB Cream Shadow really excels in terms longevity, blendability, and sun protection. Bravo!", "By the way, if you're curious what \"BB\" buzz is all about, check out this article."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 634}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/extra-lasting-eyeshadow-ink/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Extra Lasting Eyeshadow Ink", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Avon", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "7.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/3072735B-8511-4546-BAF5-E4B5DF9C2373_AvonEyeshadowInk.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Avon's Extra Lasting Eyeshadow Ink promises hours and hours of wear, and while it does live up to that claim, there are other aspects of its performance that make it less compelling.", "Described as a cream-gel eyeshadow, it comes in a small glass pot with a screw-top lid. The texture isn't quite what you might expect, as most other cream-gel shadows are soft, smooth, and easily pliable. This one is actually a bit hard, and must be warmed up with your finger before you apply it.", "That somewhat hard texture makes application tricky, as this shadow tends to stay where you put it instead of smoothing out across lids while blending. The color quality is quite strong, and that means you don't need to use a lot of this shadow to get it to show up.", "This shadow also doesn't live up to another of its claims: It isn't crease-proof. Creasing begins about three hours into its wear time, and the metallic sheen of these shadows emphasizes the creasing.", "The shade range includes a few neutrals, as well as purple, pink, and teal shades that are about as far from subtle as you can get. This is certainly not the worst eyeshadow; it's just one without any standout qualities. You can find much better options on our list of Best Eyeshadows."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 635}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/hot-singles-eye-shadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Hot Singles Eye Shadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "NYX Cosmetics", "ingredient": "Talc,  Nylon-12,  Dimethicone,  Magnesium Stearate,  Octyldodecanol,  Bis-Diglyceryl Polyacyladipate-2,  Octyldodecyl Stearoyl Stearate,  Cetyl Dimethicone,  Phenoxyethanol,  Caprylyl Glycol,  Tocopheryl Acetate. May Contain (+/-): Mica,  Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891),  Iron Oxides (CI 77491,  77492,  77499),  Ferric Ferrocyanide (CI 77510),  Manganese Violet (CI 77742),  Ultramarines (CI 77007),  Carmine (CI 75470),  Aluminum Powder (CI 77000),  Blue 1 Lake (CI 42090),  Yellow 5 Lake (CI 19140),  Black 2 (CI 77266). NOTE: Ingredients may vary by shade from the above listing.", "size": "", "price": "4.50", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/45157A76-02D4-4AF6-97C2-5462CA78E424_nyx_cosmetics_hot_singles_eye_shadow.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["Hot Singles are touted as highly pigmented eyeshadows that come in 80+ shades for any occasion. We discovered that the level of pigmentation actually varies by shade, but for the most part you can count on saturated color (especially with the deeper shades). The brighter/trendier colors are the exception as those tend to go on more sheer, taking extra effort to build color, but that's not a total deal breaker since the pressed powder texture is conducive to layering for more pigmentation.", "There are plenty of attractive colors to choose from in shimmer, metallic and matte finishes, but watch out for the glittery shades as those have a slightly coarse texture and can flake a bit (which is pretty typical of glitter-flecked shadows in general). Otherwise you can count on super-smooth blendability and durable wear throughout the day\u2014all wonderful traits for such a low price!", "In addition to classic colors you'll also find trendy hues, including neons, but as mentioned above, those shades don't always look as vibrant as they appear in the compact. Fortunately, stores such as Ulta (a major retailer of NYX Cosmetics) have testers so you can try before you buy.", "All in all, these fragrance-free shadows perform well, and at this price you can pick up several shadows without breaking the bank.  As an added bonus, the matte shades in neutral to brown and black tones also work convincingly for filling in eyebrows or for use as powder eyeliner. Gotta love a dual purpose product!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 636}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/double-take-eye-marker-and-creme-shadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Double Take Eye Marker and Creme Shadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Flower Beauty", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "9.98", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/F2FBEF48-6CB4-4044-87E3-0C24FD6E6EB2_flower-beauty.jpg?w=285", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Double Take Eye Marker and Creme Shadow is another of Flower Beauty's 2-in-1 products. We appreciate the brand's multitasking approach, but sometimes it's better to have a single product that performs well instead of two that are just mediocre!", "This product comes in a single tube with a marker-style eyeliner on one end and a creme eyeshadow with a sponge-tip applicator on the other. The liner portion has a fine-tip point that makes lining a breeze, and the formula dries quickly enough that there's no concern about smudging when you put it on. The liner is an inky black color in all the Double Take options, making it good for a classic cat-eye look. It wears well most of the day, but does start to fade after several hours.", "The creme shadow portion of this product is more problematic. You're supposed to apply it with the sponge-tip wand, and that's easy enough, but blending it with your fingers is a bit trickier. Although this is a creme, it has an almost chalky consistency that makes smoothing it across lids difficult, resulting in an uneven look, even though the color quality is strong.", "Of the three shades available, all have sparkle, and the longer you wear these shadows the more the sparkle starts to migrate to other areas of your face. As mentioned, the color selection is limited to three - purple, blue, and green - no neutrals to be found here!", "All in all, although this seems like a good idea as far as makeup multitasking goes, give this one a pass and look for better-performing liners and shadows, either together or sold separately."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 637}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/color-play-creme-eyeshadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Color Play Creme Eyeshadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Flower Beauty", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "7.98", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/2CBA42D4-DCEA-4949-BB89-1191B691A587_flower_beauty_color_play_creme_eyeshadow.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["The first thing we have to address about Flower Beauty's Color Play Creme Eyeshadow is the claim on the brand's website that this formula contains vitamin E for antioxidant protection. The truth is that while this shadow does contain a small amount of vitamin E, the fact that it's packaged in a clear jar means that any antioxidant benefit will start to diminish the instant you open it up (antioxidants don't play well when repeatedly exposed to light and air). Ignore those claims and just appreciate this for what it is: an excellent cream eyeshadow!", "Color Play has a remarkably light texture that's somewhere between a cream and a mousse, which makes it incredibly easy to smooth across eyelids and blend. The texture remains pliable enough to create the eye design you want, but isn't so moveable that it slides all over the place when you're done. It dries down to a soft powder finish that doesn't budge once it's set.", "These shadows don't crease or fade throughout the day - even a long day - and they don't flake under your eyes, either. Confession time: One of our team members accidentally fell asleep with Color Play on her lids one evening (which we most certainly do not recommend, as sleeping in eye makeup is a great way to wake up with puffy, red eyes!), but the next morning when she got up, it was still in place, right where she had put it the night before - a good indication as to this shadow's staying power!", "All of these shadows have a metallic finish, so if that doesn't interest you, these aren't the eyeshadows to focus on. Otherwise, these are cream shadows done well, and for a great price, too!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 638}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eyes-on-the-prize-eyeshadow-chubby/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Eyes On The Prize Eyeshadow Chubby", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Flower Beauty", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "7.98", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/3CFEBF57-AF6F-4620-81EB-AE699D56C09E_FlowerEyesOnThePrizeEyeshadowChubby.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Flower Beauty's Eyes On The Prize Eyeshadow Chubby is supposed to be a convenient and long-lasting shadow option for those on the go, but it's simply not what it's made out to be!", "These twist-up stick cream shadows are very similar to Clinique's mediocre Chubby Stick Shadow Tint for Eyes. The creamy formula means this glides across eyelids smoothly and is easy to blend. The color quality itself is good, and it takes only a few swipes to achieve full-color impact.", "The problems start with this shadow's wear time. Within an hour or so, it starts to crease, and fading occurs about three to four hours in, so this definitely doesn't live up to claims that it will stick around on your lids all day!", "There's also the issue that the color options, with the exception of one neutral golden beige shade, are purple, teal, olive green, and indigo - nary a neutral shade in sight! These bolder colors also make it much more noticeable when Eyes On The Prize starts to crease and fade.", "We advise skipping this and checking out one of the superior cream shadow options on our list of Best Eyeshadows."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 639}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/style-eye-con-no-3-plush-shadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Style Eye-Con No. 3 Plush Shadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Marc Jacobs Beauty", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "42.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/769B3F70-980F-4F39-8A75-E0B003E2D43E_MarcJacobs_StyleEyeConshadow.jpg?w=450", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Style Eye-Con No. 3 palettes are made up of three pressed powder eyeshadows in varying color families. Each set comes with one matte shade and two metallic/shimmer shades. The lightest shade in each set is the largest in size (the logic being that you will use that the most, typically as a base shade).", "These shadows are resistant to creasing, flaking, and fading and blend well no matter which color you use. The matte shades are a bit on the powdery side and can sometimes sheer out upon application so you may have to layer them, but the deeper the shade, the better the pigment coverage on skin.", "The color combos are a matter of personal preference. The Ingenue and Glam shades are the most universally flattering, made up of neutral nudes and browns. The Punk palette is purple-based. The Rebel palette contains a warm ivory, deep pink, and dark grayish purple. The Shoe Gazer palette comes with bronze sheen, taupe brown, and light turquoise blue. The Mod palette is made up of white, black and gray, which is about as high contrast as it gets!", "Overall, these palettes perform adequately. It's just a matter of whether you find one that suit you, and whether you're willing to pay the price for three powder shadows from a designer label when less expensive options are available."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 640}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/colorstay-shadowlinks/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "ColorStay ShadowLinks", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Revlon", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "2.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/F838EDF5-FB37-4F26-98C0-13499AE48237_Revlon_Shadowlinks.jpg?w=224", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["The concept behind these interchangeable eyeshadow compacts that click together to form one solid palette is cool, and as far the packaging goes, it works. But in terms of performance, ColorStay ShadowLinks left us unsatisfied.", "Why? Well, these shadows go on really sheer. You can layer them to build up color, but even then, the hard-packed, pressed powder texture tends to flake (especially the glittery shades).", "To make matters worse, the shadows don't easily adhere to a brush and apply unevenly. It's also tricky to find a true matte shade (some of the shades we picked out thinking they were matte ended up having tiny bits of sparkle).", "On the plus side, we do applaud Revlon for having a vast amount of classically neutral and trendy color options to build your own customized eyeshadow palette. Likewise, the bargain price is great, but sometimes you really do get what you pay for, and in this case that's true."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 641}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/fratboy-shadow-blush/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "FratBoy Shadow/Blush", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "TheBalm", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "21.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/53D542FF-98A4-4246-9243-578AB2D72357_31jGVGl50SL.jpg?w=350", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["One of theBalm's biggest strengths is its powder-textured makeup products, and this peachy blush is no exception!", "FratBoy has a remarkably smooth texture that's easy to pick up on a brush and swipe across cheeks. It's somewhat powdery when you run your brush over it, so will be messy if you get a bit overzealous, but it's easy enough to control with soft brush strokes.", "This blush can be applied as sheer or as intense as you choose, with good results both ways. It has an attractive satin finish and beautiful soft peach color that doesn't emphasize pores, and it wears well throughout the day without fading. Plus, it's fragrance-free!", "This is billed as an eyeshadow, too, and while the color isn't one that will work on everyone in that regard, if you choose to do so, it performs just as well on the eyes as it does on cheeks!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 642}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/overshadow-shimmering-all-mineral-eyeshadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Overshadow Shimmering All-Mineral Eyeshadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "TheBalm", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "15.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/C290A9FA-ACB8-4384-9D6A-D68969EBAA29_TheBalmOvershadow.jpg?w=491", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["The way theBalm markets this product is odd: It labels it as the \"first finely milled, all-mineral shimmer designed to go over eyeshadow.\" That sounds fancy, but in reality this is just loose-powder eyeshadow with shimmer, something that isn't rare at all! Talk about trying to make white bread sound interesting!", "The faulty hype doesn't mean this isn't a good product, however. You can definitely layer it over a matte or neutral eyeshadow for a more dramatic look, but it works well on its own, too.", "As with most loose-powder shadows, the loose nature of it means application can be a bit tricky, in that there's the potential for a mess, with powder going everywhere. We recommend tapping a bit of shadow out onto another surface, swirling it around with a brush to \"blend\" it together (instead of just having shimmery clumps), and then applying it.", "Once applied, these shadows are truly beautiful, and they blend like a dream. They have an attractive shimmer that isn't garish, last all day long without creasing or fading, and come in four neutral colors that will work for most skin tones.", "That said, there are certainly other products that do the same thing without the potential mess, but if you're interested, this is a good option to check out!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 643}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/shadow-softies-by-intense-i-color/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Shadow Softies by Intense i-Color", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Almay", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "4.49", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/68BBAAEB-214A-4DE3-BFAA-589927218A71_Almay_IntenseiColorEyeshadowSofties.jpg?w=300", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Almay's Shadow Softies by Intense I-Color is an interesting take on eye makeup in the form of what can only be described as a hybrid product. In the pan, this silicone-based, fragrance-free product looks like a typical powder eyeshadow, but after you swipe it with a brush a few times you'll notice something different beneath the surface - a cream-like texture, though this isn't a straight-up cream eyeshadow.", "The trick when applying this hybrid shadow is to use a stiff-bristled brush, not one with soft or \"fluffy\" bristles, because a stiff-bristled brush picks up this cream-powder combo well, making it much easier to apply.", "Once you've got the right tool, this applies easily with buildable color that doesn't fall onto other areas of your face. It wears well all day without creasing or fading, and removes easily with a water-soluble cleanser.", "There are a dozen shades available \u2013 six with matte finishes, six with shimmer finishes - and while a lot of them are very bright, there are some good neutrals, too, so you can mix and match based on personal preference.", "Overall, this is a good shadow option for those looking to try something different that's also affordable."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 644}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/color-coat-cream-eye-shadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Color Coat Cream Eye Shadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Ulta", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "8.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/46352348-FA84-41E0-9A7B-B1CDE767DC87_imagesCAE3A2VN.jpg?w=225", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["For a cream shadow, Color Coat has its advantages. The quick dry formula is truly crease-proof. You do have to blend it on quickly, but once set, it stays put without fading throughout the day\u2014the truest sign that you've found a cream eyeshadow worth using!", "The shade range could use some expansion, and this plus the shine overload is why it missed our top rating. As is, your only choices are shimmering/metallic hues of gold, beige, pink, blue, plum or silver. The shiny finish will exacerbate wrinkles so if that's an issue for you, pass on this. Depending on how thickly you apply them, the shades can go on sheer or deeply saturated with color.", "Although not for everyone, if you have a wrinkle-free eye area and can find a shade that suits you, this is an excellent cream shadow that goes the distance."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 645}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/pure-color-instant-intense-eyeshadow-trio/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Pure Color Instant Intense EyeShadow Trio", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Estee Lauder", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "36.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/FE387218-73DF-47B2-A956-D2298CBCCD09_EsteeLauderPureColorInstantEyeshadowTrio.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["It's not necessary to spend this much on powder eyeshadow, but if you're a big fan of Estee Lauder products, chances are you're used to those numbers by now. Part of what you're paying for is the brand's prestige and the elegant packaging.", "The overt shine is likely what Lauder is referring to by \"intense\" in this product's name because, although the colors don't go on with intense pigmentation, you definitely get intense shine! However, if strong shine with less color is your preference (though we don't know why it would be) then this is a good option to consider.", "This eyeshadow has a smooth, blendable texture and offers medium pigment that can be sheered out easily. However, as with most powder eyeshadows, the softer you blend the color, the more prone they are to fade throughout the day.", "The shade range offers some wearable options for daytime, but the shiny finish will not work well for anyone who wants eyeshadow to minimize, rather than enhance, the appearance of crepey or wrinkled eyelids."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 646}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/flamed-out-shadow-pot/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Flamed Out Shadow Pot", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "CoverGirl", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "3.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/D0FAA62F-6F56-4DE0-B744-5929B90ED46B_CovergirlFlamedOutShadowPot.jpg?w=1024", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["If you want a pressed-powder eyeshadow with a shiny finish this fits the bill, as Flamed Out Shadow Pot certainly delivers on the \"glittery and sparkly effect\" claim. Unfortunately, the glitter keeps this product from blending evenly, and that issue is worse in the darker shades, which tend to feel quite chalky.", "Still, the shine clings surprisingly well, which is good but the downside is that the shine will likely outlast the pigment, which begins to fade after about 6 hours. The majority of the shades in the collection are vibrant like Fired Up Pink and Lime Light and they work well for a more noticeable application of shadow. While the price is tempting keep in mind that these are a lower quality than equivalent products from lines like M.A.C. and NARS.", "This product is definitely not recommended for anyone with crepey or wrinkled eyelids because the high-shine finish magnifies wrinkles and less-than-taut skin."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 647}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-color-quad/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Eye Color Quad", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Tom Ford", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "82.00", "claims": "Tom Ford eyeshadow quad features four complementary shades that give you a range of looks from bold to smoky, or sexy to subtle. Each features four different finishes too, from a sheer sparkle to a satin to a shimmer to a matte so you can wear each alone or mix and match for an unforgettable look.", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/F45735B5-2CD2-4674-A0E9-194761094CC7_TomFordEyeColorQuad.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Eye Color Quad is a decent group of shadows, though certainly not the best available. Each of the quads available includes a matte, satin, shimmer, and sparkle shade. That's either a plus or a minus depending on what you think of the colors and how much shine you may or may not want from each.", "These shadows do look beautiful, and for the most part are smooth enough that they apply well without any excess shadow falling onto cheeks. The tricky part is the sparkle shade that's included in each compact - they're gorgeous once applied, but you really have to work to get it on without making a mess or having it go where you don't want it. The makeup artist we spoke with recommended not using a brush at all (as it tends to flake with this technique), but instead patting it on gently with a fingertip. This technique works well, but requires a bit more time than if you could just swipe it on with a brush.", "These shadows' color impact is good, and they wear very well with only minimal fading throughout the day. There are some beautiful combinations, which can work for a subtle daytime look or for a more dramatic nighttime look. Most of the quads have colors that are well-coordinated, although the all-blue Cobalt Rush, all-purple Crushed Amethyst, and pink and amber Burnished Amber quads are ones to watch out for. Golden Mink, Cocoa Mirage, and Silvered Topaz, however, are gorgeous!", "Overall, these are good quads, but they're absolutely not the best you can buy - especially considering the price! If you're in the market for designer powder eyeshadow sets, Dior's eyeshadows still reign supreme."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 648}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/noir-absolute-for-eyes/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Noir Absolute for Eyes", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Tom Ford", "ingredient": null, "size": "0.12 fl. oz.", "price": "36.00", "claims": "Noir Absolute for eyes is a black gel formula that's designed to sweep over your entire lid for a smoldering eye or as a subtle liner. It features highly-enriched, blackened pigments infused with a spark of blue optics to catch the light and brighten your eyes.", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/3C124D76-CF3B-4C41-92ED-F2F93C42005E_tomford2.gif?w=200", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["At first glance, Noir Absolute for Eyes looks like a gel eyeliner along the lines of MAC's Fluidline or Bobbi Brown's Gel Eyeliner. When you open up the jar though, you'll notice it's a much less creamy product, with a far drier texture than the M.A.C. or Bobbi Brown formulas. This means the best way to apply it is with a stiff, short-bristled brush rather than a pointed eyeliner brush.", "Noir Absolute comes in only one color, a midnight blue shade with subtle sparkles. (Tom Ford's website says it's black, but it is most assuredly midnight blue!). It's supposed to be dual purpose - used either smudged on the eyelid itself for a messy smokey eye look, or right along the lash line as a standard liner. We advise using it mainly as a liner though, unless you're going for a runway-edgy look that says, \"I slept in my makeup but am too beautiful to care.\"", "We admit that Noir Absolute for Eyes looks attractive (the sparkles do serve to highlight eyes) and applies easily with the right brush. However, it fades quite a bit over time - by the time we took it off at the end of the day, the outer edges of our eyeliner design were mostly worn off! You'd wind up happier using a similar but longer lasting product from M.A.C., Bobbi Brown, or Laura Mercier."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 649}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/bombshell-shineshadow-by-lashblast/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Bombshell ShineShadow by Lashblast", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "CoverGirl", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "6.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/343E7F21-6E4F-4486-A22D-CE07B06D86B8_CovergirlBombshellShineshadow.jpg?w=1024", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["These creamy eyeshadows live up to their name in that the finish is very, very shiny; and we certainly wouldn't expect anything less from a product called ShineShadow! Of course, not everyone will want their lids to shine this brightly, but if you do, then this is an OK option because the shine clings surprisingly well.", "The texture blends smoothly and the colors provide medium pigment with even coverage. The main disappointment, which is what keeps this product from rating higher, is that while the glitter stays put, the actual color tends to fade and crease after only a few hours. Talk about mixed results!", "The shade selection is limited to pastels and a few earth tones, so if you remain keen on trying this, choose carefully: We suggest the charcoal gray or the pale pink colors."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 650}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/studio-baked-eyeshadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Studio Baked Eyeshadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "e.l.f. Cosmetics", "ingredient": "Mica,  Talc,  Bismuth Oxychloride,  Ethylhexyl Palmitate,  Paraffinum Liquidum (mineral oil),  Dimethicone,  Magnesium Aluminum Silicate,  Tocopheryl Acetate,  Simmondsia Chinensis (Jojoba) Seed Oil,  Rosa Canina (Rose Hip) Fruit Oil,  Helianthus Annuus (Sunflower) Seed Oil,  Prunus Armeniaca (Apricot) Kernel Oil,  Vitis Vinifera (Grape) Seed Oil,  Phenoxyethanol,  Methylparaben. May Contain: Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891),  Iron Oxides (CI 77491 ,  CI 77492 ,  CI 77499),  Ultramarine Violet (CI 77077),  Manganese Violet (CI 77742),  Ferric Ferrocyanide (CI 77510),  Tin Oxide (CI 77861),  Yellow No.5 Lake (CI 19140),  Red No.40 Lake (CI 16035),  Blue No.1 Lake (CI 42090). NOTE: Ingredients may vary by shade from the above listing.", "size": "", "price": "3.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/B313D241-1640-442B-ADDD-EE1E67D60EBA_ELFBakedEyeShadow.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["e.l.f.'s Studio Baked Eyeshadow is a true beauty bargain! For just a few dollars, you get a powder eyeshadow that performs just as well, or even better than, its higher-end counterparts. Score!", "Studio Baked Eyeshadow has a soft, silky texture that's easy to pick up on your shadow brush, and it glides smoothly across the eyelids. A little bit provides sheer color impact that can be built up with ease because it's not too powdery, which means it doesn't migrate all over your cheeks or eyelashes if you pile it on.", "This shadow wears well throughout the day without creasing or fading, and comes in a small but well-chosen variety of colors, including several neutral options, such as Enchanted and Bark. Each shade does have a certain amount of shimmer, so that's something to consider if that's not your preference. Otherwise, this is a great shadow and a great buy!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 651}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/scandaleyes-stick/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "ScandalEyes Stick", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Rimmel", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "3.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/B095292D-6404-4ECA-ACC7-DE6B4B8F075D_RimmelScandaleyesStick.jpg?w=1000", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Rimmel London promises its ScandalEyes Stick has \"high impact color that's easy to apply.\" Although that's true, there are drawbacks that make this only an average cream eyeshadow option.", "Presented in pencil form, this eyeshadow's creaminess helps it glide easily with no tugging. The color quality is good, and you don't need a lot to get full-color impact. This also doesn't fade as the day wears on.", "Unfortunately, the formula tends to crease! You'll start to notice creasing on your lids a few hours in, which is definitely not attractive. Add to that the fact that this pencil needs sharpening (which wastes product), and you're better off checking out our list of Best Eyeshadows instead."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 652}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/master-smoky-longwearing-shadow-pencil/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Master Smoky Longwearing Shadow-Pencil", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Maybelline New York", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "6.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/8D765812-7D0E-4719-83C9-943C268DBBD2_MaybellineMasterSmoky.jpg?w=96", "expert_rating": "1", "expert_reviews": ["Maybelline's Master Smoky Longwearing Shadow-Pencil has a great concept\u2014an eyeshadow stick that includes its own smudging tool\u2014unfortunately, execution is just a mess all the way around! On one end of this pencil is a twist-up eyeshadow stick; on the other end a round sponge applicator that's supposed to smudge the shadow for a perfect smokey eye.", "The problems start right away with application. The pencil texture is a bit hard, so you have to tug and drag it across your eyelid to get any sort of color impact\u2014this is not an easy \"swipe across the eye\" product! The shadow stays put where you apply it, which means blending is very difficult, even with the included smudging tool. In fact, the smudging tool is pretty much useless\u2014a light hand doesn't smudge at all, and pressing down heavier on it only serves to tug even more at the eyelids, while at the same time wiping off some of the product! Talk about wax on, wax off!", "Avoid this gimmicky product; there are plenty of others out there that you can use to achieve a classic smokey eye without abusing your eyelids!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 653}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/stay-perfect-eye-shadow-duo/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Stay Perfect Eye Shadow Duo", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Boots", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "6.49", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/7ED0A15F-87FE-421C-8EA1-A5D425A33831_51-2Br-16x1sL.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["There are some misses among the color pairings of these duos, but overall, the collection offers more to like than dislike. The silky-smooth texture makes application nearly effortless and the pigment is good. All shades have some amount of shine, but no obvious glitter or flaking. Although sheer, the color does stay on well.", "For more pronounced color payoff and longer wear, these shadows can be paired with a primer, as you would to enhance any other powder eyeshadow. The shade range is limited, and only Mother Earth and Moonlight Shadows are recommended.", "Note: As far as Boots' eyeshadows go, their singles are a better option because they offer more color options and, unlike the duos, there are matte finishes available."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 654}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-paint/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Eye Paint", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "NARS", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "25.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/7FE7275A-7A55-45EA-9A08-7496400B033D_NARS_EyePaint.jpg?w=300", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["These creamy, full-coverage eye colors can be used as eyeshadow or eyeliner, but work best as eyeliner. There are a few reasons for this, but mainly it's that the color selection is very dark, which limits the types of eye designs that can be created with this product. Also, the glitter finish is much more noticeable when Eye Paint is applied all over the lid, not a look everyone will appreciate. As an eyeliner, NARS Eye Paint applies evenly without feathering and lasts for several hours without smudging.", "As an overall color, the creamy texture still applies and blends well, but the color begins to crease and fade within a few hours of wear (especially on oily eyelids). It doesn't even come close to living up to the 18-hour wear claim! Sure, you could pair this product with a primer or set it with a powder, but that's more work than should be required from a product like this. If the concept of Eye Paint appeals to you, M.A.C. does it better with their Paint products for eyes."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 655}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/all-about-shadow-singles/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "All About Shadow Singles", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Clinique", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "15.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/7F76ACD8-C736-406F-9B41-851E8F7A5110_Clinique_AllAboutShadowSingle.jpg?w=300", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Clinique's latest eyeshadow, All About Shadow Singles, was announced with much fanfare, but beneath the hype and the pretty ads, these powder shadows aren't very impressive.", "Three different textures are available: Soft Matte (which is truly matte), Soft Shimmer, and Super Shimmer. Each finish comes in a wide variety of shades, including some true neutrals and some bold purples, pinks, and blues.", "All of the All About Shadow Singles feel smooth in the pan and apply easily, but (with the exception of the very black Stroke of Midnight) the color impact is so light that you have to pack quite a bit of product on to actually tell you're wearing it. Because this shadow must be applied so heavily, you can wind up with an excess of powder that falls onto the tops of your cheekbones, which you then have to dust off.", "All About Shadow Singles wears well for several hours, with some fading around the six-hour mark. This isn't a terrible eyeshadow, but you can find much better options at the department store and the drugstore!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 656}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/color-tattoo-pure-pigments/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews ", "product_names": "Color Tattoo Pure Pigments", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Maybelline New York", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "5.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/3B5E5220-4AEB-439F-A346-C1648BA9B1C9_510aJzXMMfL.jpg?w=498", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["These loose-powder eyeshadow pigments can be a mess to use because of the jar packaging, but they apply beautifully and offer excellent buildable color payoff.", "All the shades blend and cling surprisingly well. Mica lends these pigments a very shiny finish, so if you don't want high shine with your eyeshadows these aren't for you. On the other hand, if you like shimmer, they're definitely worth considering.", "Similar to many loose pigments from artistry-themed makeup lines, Maybelline's range includes eye-catching brights such as blue, purple, and canary yellow, which can be used to achieve a variety of startling effects. However, the most wearable everyday shades are Barely Brazen, Buff & Tuff, Breaking Bronze, and Improper Copper."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 657}
