thly. The color quality starts off sheer, but can be built up for a much more intense look. This wears very well, with no significant fading even after several hours of wear.", "One of the best features is that this doesn't suffer the curse of many powder eyeshadows\u2014it doesn't fall onto the tops of your cheeks when you put it on! It stays right where you put it, even the sparkly shades.", "I-Mark comes in a wide variety of colors, from staple neutrals to bright pinks and purples, for those who are inclined to use such shades. Some truly matte shades are also available, and these can easily double as eyeliners.", "One thing to note: Avon Mark doesn't list on its website whether the shade you're considering is shiny or matte, so it's a good idea to call Avon or visit your local Avon Mark representative to make sure you're getting exactly what you want!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 663}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-amplifying-shadow-liner/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews%26p%3D2 ", "product_names": "Eye Amplifying Shadow Liner", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Mally Beauty", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "20.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/5760CE8D-FE48-4EE2-98E2-76AA099EDC33_31TUNxKkbzL.jpg?w=341", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["These waterproof eyeshadow pencils go on thick and apply very rich, opaque color. The high-shimmer finish borders on metallic, which may indeed \"amplify\" the eyes, but it also amplifies the appearance of any creases or wrinkles on the eyelids, and there are no matte-finish options available.", "Another hard-to-ignore drawback is that these pencils require sharpening every time the tip smushes down or breaks off. The creamy tip breaks easily, so unless you're very careful, you'll be sharpening frequently.", "Although these pencils are supposed to double as eyeliners, they don't work well for that purpose. The pencil tip is too large for controlled application near the eyelashes and the creamy texture smudges too easily."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 664}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-perfection-weightless-shadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews%26p%3D2 ", "product_names": "Eye Perfection Weightless Shadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Mally Beauty", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "25.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/3CB6E8F7-905E-46A4-9BD2-8894104ABABE_31zSPfVsqyL.jpg?w=300", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["As much as we like this loose-powder eyeshadow because of its formula and performance, the packaging is too big a problem to ignore. A small sponge-tip brush is built into the cap and because the cap is spring-loaded the loose powder puffs out whenever the cap is opened\u2014wasting product and creating a mess.", "If you happen to prefer loose-powder to pressed-powder eyeshadows and have the patience to deal with this one's poor packaging, the actual powder itself is quite good. Its butter-soft texture is a pleasure to blend, and it wears nicely throughout the day.", "These shadows come in shimmery neutral shades that work well as a base or as an allover shade, which is how we suggest using them. The built-in brush is too clumsy for creating intricate eye designs, and the packaging makes it very difficult to use the product with a different brush\u2014another drawback to keep in mind."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 665}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-shadow-single/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews%26p%3D2 ", "product_names": "Eye Shadow Single", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Cargo Cosmetics", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "16.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/0C363FEE-C874-4CD8-B006-2BFA5E5615EC_Cargo_EyeShadow.jpg?w=342", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["For a makeup-centric line, Cargo had very little in the way of eyeshadow options, so it's a good thing they've added some single powder eyeshadow options. Unfortunately, this addition is simply average.", "The shadows come in about a dozen shades, most of them neutral, and almost all contain some level of shimmer (there's only one truly matte version in the bunch). The shadow shades are pigment-rich\u2014 it doesn't take much to get a healthy dose of color\u2014but despite long-wearing claims, the color tends to fade over time. Also, when you're applying it, it's a bit messy \u2013 the powder falls all over lashes, even after you knock excess powder off your shadow brush. You're much better off checking out some of the products on our list of Best Eyeshadows."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 666}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/longwear-powder-shadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews%26p%3D2 ", "product_names": "Longwear Powder Shadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Benefit", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "20.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/391125BA-98AD-40BB-97D9-46865B477FB4_51ivN0-2BeE8L.jpg?w=450", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Longwear Powder Shadow isn't a bad eyeshadow by any means; it's just nothing special and overpriced for what you get. Benefit claims this shadow is long-wearing and that's true \u2013 it lasts several hours without fading, and that's always a good thing, but certainly not unique to this product!", "Though the color selection is relatively small, it boasts a nice variety of shades and three different finishes \u2013 matte, satin, and sheen. Regardless of the finish you choose (and each is named accurately in terms of how it looks when applied), the main failing of this shadow is that it's a bit too powdery. Swiping your brush across the shadow pan causes a small swirl of powder dust (which shouldn't be the case, even for a powder product), and the powder has a tendency to fall onto the top of cheeks as you apply it, even after knocking excess powder off your brush. Not so bad if you're using one of the paler shades, but a definite drawback if you choose a darker color!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 667}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/intense-i-color-liquid-shadow-color-primer/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-reviews%26p%3D2 ", "product_names": "Intense i-Color Liquid Shadow + Color Primer", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow", "brand": "Almay", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "7.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/897FDE15-F5F1-4B59-BB98-3EF81668FA06_Almay_IntenseiColorPrimer.jpg?w=152", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Almay advertises Intense I-Color Liquid Shadow + Color Primer as a revolutionary product, but when it comes right down to it, it's about as revolutionary as white bread! The only thing intense about it is the name.", "This liquid shadow comes with a wand applicator that you're supposed to swipe over the eyelids. The shadow itself is pretty sheer with some subtle shimmer, and it takes a few swipes to get it to really show up.", "Like most Almay Intense I-Color eye products, this comes color-coded for brown, blue, hazel, and green eyes. Although the eyeshadow color you choose can indeed enhance your natural eye color, in this case Almay's colors aren't all that logical. For example, if you have blue eyes you're directed to use the Sky Blue shade, thus putting blue next to blue. The problem? This isn't a case where like enhances like; rather, if you want to enhance your eye color, choose a contrasting or neutral color rather than a matching shade. So, for blue eyes, go for a soft peach or cantaloupe color, or any shade of soft brown\u2014definitely not blue! In the real world of fashion, eye makeup is about shaping the eye with neutral tones, not wearing color. Want proof? Just look at any cover of a fashion magazine.", "The shadow doesn't crease during the day, but fades a bit after a few hours. As a primer for other shadows, the sheerness allows other colors to be put over it without a \"muddy\" looking result, but it doesn't make any significant difference in the amount of wear time for the shadow you put over it. Overall, this is just very average and offers very few to no real benefit."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 668}
