Stearate,  Sodium Dehydroacetate,  Phenoxyethanol,  Sorbic Acid. All Shades May Contain: Mica,  Titanium Dioxide,  Iron Oxides,  Carmine,  Aluminum Powder,  Ultramarines,  Bismuth Oxychloride,  Bronze Powder,  Copper Powder,  Ferric Ammonium Ferrocyanide,  Ferric Ferrocyanide,  Manganese Violet.", "size": "0.60 fl. oz.", "price": "54.00", "claims": "We packed this palette with a dozen sultry, smoky neutrals, including nine never-before-seen shades and three exclusives from past palettes. Experiment with warm bronzes, dimensional grays, rich browns, gorgeous taupes and deep black. From mattes and satins to shades with sparkle, Naked Smoky has it all!", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/97DA852C-BA05-467C-A5D4-135CFCE0516D_UrbanDecay-Naked-Smoky-Palette-sq.png?w=600", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["Urban Decay's Naked eyeshadows palettes have always garnered quite a bit of fanfare around their launch, but does the Naked Smoky Eyeshadow Palette live up to that hype? Actually, it does!", "With nine new shades and three carried over from previous Urban Decay palettes, the Naked Smoky Eyeshadow Palette leans toward mostly cool tones in varying finishes of shimmer, micro-glitter, and matte. In addition to the nude and brown hues, there are also deeply pigmented variations of plum, blue, and slate grey, as well as a satin black shade to round out the smoky look. The lighter shades tend to go on more sheer, which makes them great for layering.", "Most of the shades have a smooth texture that makes blending a breeze and fallout was practically nonexistent. A couple of the semi-glittery shades do flake a smidge (particularly \"Armor\"), but we found an eyeshadow primer helped solidify their wear. (We used Urban Decay's Original Primer Potion.)", "The included dual-ended brush has a fluffy \"crease\" brush on one end and a rounded, stubby \"smudging\" brush with soft, but dense, hairs on the other. Both work well for their intended purpose, and if you're traveling, it's enough to get you by.", "Combined these 12 shadows offer versatility for creating various sultry eyeshadow designs as well as softer daytime looks. The richly pigmented shades lend themselves to creating a smoky eye, and if you're into switching up your eyeshadow look on a regular basis, the Naked Smoky Eyeshadow Palette is a great way to go! Kudos to Urban Decay for creating another great eyeshadow palette", "FYI: All of the shades are fragrance-free."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 849}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/luxury-palette-colour-coded-eyeshadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Luxury Palette Colour-Coded Eyeshadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Charlotte Tilbury", "ingredient": "Talc,  Mica,  Calcium Sodium Borosilicate,  Octyldodecyl Stearoyl Stearate,  Dimethicone,  Zinc Stearate,  Calcium Aluminum Borosilicate,  Diisostearyl Malate,  Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride,  Zea Mays (Corn) Starch,  Silica,  Hydrogenated Castor Oil Hydroxystearate,  Pentaerythrityl Tetraisostearate,  Potassium Sorbate,  Chlorphenesin,  Polyethylene,  Isononyl Isononanoate,  1, 2-Hexanediol,  Caprylyl Glycol,  Tin Oxide,  Caprylyl Methicone,  Tetrasodium EDTA,  Zeolite,  Dimethiconol,  Sorbic Acid,  Methylparaben,  Propylparaben,  Butylparaben,  BHT,  Trimethylsiloxysilicate,  [May Contain: Ultramarines CI 77007,  Carmine CI 75470,  Ferric Ammonium Ferrocyanide CI 77510,  Ferric Ferrocyanide CI 77510,  Blue 1 Lake CI 42090,  Titanium Dioxide CI 77891,  Manganese Violet CI 77742,  Iron Oxides CI 77492,  Iron Oxides CI 77499,  Iron Oxides CI 77491]. *Note: This ingredient list is taken directly from the product packaging.", "size": "0.18 fl. oz.", "price": "52.00", "claims": "The power to mesmerize is in your eyes, with this makeup hypnotize I have de-coded the secrets to iconic, mesmerizing eyes with my Color-Coded Eyeshadow Palettes. Each one contains four harmonious shades that offer a complete desk to disco eye color wardrobe and an easy to use application ritual that is fail-safe to follow. Its my artistry made easy!\n", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/C45DA8C2-5390-46D7-AC2C-2DEF840D2FCE_Charlotte-Tilbury-Luxury-Eyeshadow-Palette-sq.png?w=600", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["Charlotte Tilbury's Luxury Palette Colour-Coded Eyeshadow is the brand's take on a popular eyeshadow concept: A four-shade collection designed to create a complete eye look with just one product. We're glad to say that this gets a lot right! Thanks to great texture, wear time, and overall performance, this easily earns our highest rating.", "Each palette comes in a square-shaped compact in Charlotte Tilbury's signature rose-gold packaging. Four color-coordinated, fragrance-free shades are featured: A lighter all-over base shade (which can also be used as a highlight on the brow bone), a crease shade, a lid shade, and a shade for the \"outer-v\" of the eyes\u2014though of course you can use them as you choose. While these shadows are in powder form, they have an almost creamy consistency that makes them easy to pick up on your makeup brush, and they're easy to apply and blend.", "The only minor quibble we have is that the initial application is a bit sheer, but each shade can be easily built up for a stronger color impact.", "Where this collection of palettes really shines is in its performance. We found that it did not fade or crease throughout a workday\u2014and this was true of even the glitteriest shades! In fact, the glitter shades were impressive in that they applied just as smoothly as the matte options, with no fallout, even after a full day of wear. We also found that the glitter was on the subtler side, and is workable for a daytime look should you choose to wear it that way.", "Charlotte Tilbury offers Luxury Palette Colour-Coded Eyeshadow in a good variety of different color and finish combinations. Among the current options are an all-matte selection of neutrals (\"The Sophisticate\"), an all-glitter/shimmer option (\"The Uptown Girl\"), and several palettes that combine finishes for a multi-dimensional look. Even better, all of the options are attractive and range from colors suitable for daily wear to more dramatic nighttime looks.", "Overall, though it certainly isn't the least expensive option available, thanks to its exceptional performance and shade variety, Charlotte Tilbury's Luxury Palette Colour-Coded Eyeshadow is certainly a worthy one\u2014and the collection is one we happily recommend checking out!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 850}
