 Ferric Ferrocyanide. Exposure (Plums) -- Shade 1,  2,  4: Mica,  Talc,  Triethylhexanoin,  Boron Nitride,  Zinc Stearate,  Lauroyl Lysine,  Tocopheryl Acetate,  Nylon-12,  Silica,  Magnesium Carbonate,  Caprylyl Glycol,  Hexylene Glycol,  Phenoxyethanol. May Contain (+/-): Titanium Dioxide,  Iron Oxides,  Carmine,  Ultramarines; Shade 3: Mica,  Triethylhexanoin,  Talc,  Zinc Stearate,  Boron Nitride,  Silica,  Lauroyl Lysine,  Tocopheryl Acetate,  Nylon-12,  Magnesium Carbonate,  Isopropyl Titanium Triisostearate,  Triethoxycaprylylsilane,  Caprylyl Glycol,  Hexylene Glycol,  Phenoxyethanol. May Contain (+/-): Titanium Dioxide,  Iron Oxides; Shade 5: Mica,  Zinc Stearate,  Silica,  Lauroyl Lysine,  Squalane Dimethicone,  Hydrogenated Lecithin,  Trimyristin,  Caprylyl Glycol,  Hexylene Glycol,  Phenoxyethanol. May Contain (+/-): Titanium Dioxide,  Iron Oxides,  Ultramarines,  Carmine,  Manganese Violet,  Yellow 5 Lake. Color Field (Olive) -- Shade 1: Mica,  Kaolin,  Zinc Stearate,  Silica,  Lauroyl Lysine,  Squalane,  Dimethicone,  Hydrogenated Lecithin,  Trimyristin,  Caprylyl Glycol,  Hexylene Glycol,  Phenoxyethanol. May Contain (+/-): Titanium Dioxide,  Iron Oxides; Shade 2,  3,  4,  5: Mica,  Talc,  Triethylhexanoin,  Boron Nitride,  Zinc Stearate,  Lauroyl Lysine,  Tocopheryl Acetate,  Nylon-12,  Silica,  Magnesium Carbonate,  Caprylyl Glycol,  Hexylene Glycol,  Phenoxyethanol. May Contain (+/-): Titanium Dioxide,  Iron Oxides,  Chromium Oxide Greens. Atmosphere (Cool Neutrals) -- Shade 1,  4,  5: Mica,  Zinc Stearate,  Silica,  Lauroyl Lysine,  Squalane,  Dimethicone,  Hydrogenated Lecithin,  Trimyristin,  Caprylyl Glycol,  Hexylene Glycol,  Phenoxyethanol. May Contain (+/-): Iron Oxides,  Carmine; Shade 2: Mica,  Talc,  Triethylhexanoin,  Boron Nitride,  Zinc Stearate,  Lauroyl Lysine,  Tocopheryl Acetate,  Nylon-12,  Silica,  Magnesium Carbonate,  Caprylyl Glycol,  Hexylene Glycol,  Phenoxyethanol. May Contain (+/): Titanium Dioxide,  Iron Oxides,  Carmine; Shade 3: Mica,  Kaolin,  Zinc Stearate,  Squalane,  Silica,  Dimethicone,  Lauroyl Lysine,  Hydrogenated Lecithin,  Trimyristin,  Caprylyl Glycol,  Hexylene Glycol,  Phenoxyethanol. May Contain (+/-): Titaium Dioxide,  Iron Oxides,  Ultramarines.", "size": "5.00 grams", "price": "58.00", "claims": "An artist-inspired eye shadow palette with seamless color transitionsoffering effortlessly blendable and wearable shades in a range of finishes and textures.", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/15C2EDFF-C07C-475B-9653-0420D0F29CF2_HourglassModernistEyeshadowPalette.jpg?w=1024", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Hourglass certainly knows what it's doing when it comes to product packaging! The Modernist series of palettes is gorgeous: Each contains five powder shadow colors arranged in a wave-like pattern that looks like sand art in a sleek, attractive compact. But does a pretty palette equal pretty performance? Unfortunately in this case, the answer is no!", "The main issue is the sparkly metallic shade included in almost every palette (save for the Atmosphere palette, whose shades are a mix of matte and satin matte finishes). Whether or not sparkle is your goal, no one wants a poorly performing shadow\u2014the Modernist's sparkle formula flakes throughout the day, leaving you with noticeable flecks of shadow on the tops of your cheekbones and under your eyes by the time you're ready to remove your makeup.", "Hourglass is correct when it says these shadows are incredibly soft. They have a buttery, almost cream-like texture that's easy to pick up on your brush, and the color quality is strong. But blendability is a problem with all of these shadows regardless of their finish.", "The blending issue is particularly true of the darker shades in each palette, which tend to cling unevenly to the areas where you apply them, leading to a blotchy look. You can blend them with a light, fluffy brush, but it takes some work! Once blended, these shadows last about seven hours without fading.", "All the palettes feature mostly neutral colors and attractive shade combinations. For all the hype though, this is just an average product due to the issues with blending and flaking. You'll find much better options (both in single and palette form) on our list of Best Eyeshadows.", "Check out the video review", "Pros:", "Cons:"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 852}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/les-4-ombres-multi-effect-quadra-eyeshadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Les 4 Ombres Multi-Effect Quadra Eyeshadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Chanel", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "61.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/D20FA2FE-6617-477F-98EF-756220E71EF8_chanellogo.gif?w=112", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["A Chanel staple for years, Les 4 Ombres De Chanel Quadra Eyeshadow has been revamped into an even glitzier version: Les 4 Ombres Multi-Effect Quadra Eyeshadow. Currently, both the new and original versions are being sold side by side, both online and in-store, which can get a little confusing because they aren't differentiated very well, unless you're in the know. To help clear up the confusion when you're shopping, the powder shadows in the new Multi-Effect version of Les 4 Ombres Eyeshadows are circular rather than the original's square shape.", "Note: The Chanel representatives we spoke with assured us that the original formula isn't going away (at least for now).", "Similar to its predecessor, Les 4 Ombres Multi-Effect Quadra Eyeshadow has an enviable silky, pressed-powder texture, although this time it feels almost creamy. Just like the original, these fragrance-free shadows blend on like butter, making even application a breeze. The difference is that these shades are even more intensely shiny, some bordering on '70s sequined glitterball shine; for the most part, you get more shine than you do color. On the upside, the glitter and shimmer cling well to the skin without noticeable flaking; however, we did notice that the color fades a bit as the day wears on.", "Each quad is designed around the concept of offering two medium-tone shades, a deep shadow to intensify and a light shade to highlight. While there are certainly some attractive color combinations, we really wish there were at least one matte shade in each set. As is, those with crepey eyelids will notice that the shine exacerbates their wrinkly skin.", "In the end, if you're looking for a shimmery, sparkly, dazzling eyeshadow quad, Les 4 Ombres Multi-Effect Quadra Eyeshadow fits the bill. But if obvious shine isn't your thing or you don't want to draw attention to wrinkly eyelids, we recommend looking elsewhere."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 853}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/expert-wear-the-nudes-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Expert Wear The Nudes Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Maybelline New York", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "9.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/87B634C6-F3BF-46ED-855B-334E8B7F7A55_MaybellineTheNudesPalette.jpg?w=1024", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["There are a lot of nude eyeshadow palettes out there these days, and with good reason: A variety of neutral shades in one convenient package can be a great addition to just about any makeup kit! Adding to the list of options is Expert Wear The Nudes Palette from Maybelline. So how does it stack up?", "This inexpensive palette comes in a sleek-looking, flat black compact, and features 12 shades of cream, brown-toned, copper, and black shadows. Some of the shades have true matte finishes, while others have satin or shimmer finishes (there are no glittery shades to be found here). All of the shades are attractive and neutral (\"nude\") enough that they'll be useful for a wide variety of looks, from subtle daytime looks to dramatic nighttime makeup.", "The texture of the shadows is smooth and somewhat powdery, but not to the point where you get dust clouds when you apply them. They're easy to pick up on a brush (ignore the outdated plastic sponge-tipped applicator that comes with this, as it simply isn't effective), and color quality is good, meaning you don't have to pack it on too much to get the colors to show up.", "The problem here is that they're somewhat difficult to blend. The shadows tend to stay exactly where you put them, which make for a messy look, especially because some of these colors are quite dark! It's not impossible to blend these; it's just that it takes some time to do so; these simply don't have the gorgeous blendability of today's best eyeshadow palettes.", "Another issue is that these shadows start to fade about halfway through a standard 8-hour workday. An eyeshadow primer can extend the wear for a little bit, but the best eyeshadows should be able to hang in there, regardless of whether there's a primer under them or not!", "In the end this isn't a terrible palette, it's just one that isn't impressive, despite its affordable price."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 854}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/the-eyeshadow-smooth-eye-color-quad/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "The Eyeshadow Smooth Eye Color Quad", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Dolce & Gabbana", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "60.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/9E2FF1CE-2818-4AE9-BBAF-9347177B1BE4_dolce-and-gabbana-official.jpg?w=229", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["This fragrance-free powder eyeshadow quad offers a silky-soft texture that blends smoothly across the eye area and holds up well throughout the day without flaking or fading.", "The color combos are hit or miss, but there are some attractive options to explore. Opacity varies among the four shades in each set, but most of them consistently offer what's best described as a mid-level sheerness that can be layered for more intensity. There is also a contrast among the finish of the colors in each quad, ranging from matte to metallic or satin.", "Smooth Eye Color Quad beams with elegance from the outside with its decadent, golden Dolce & Gabbana case and performs adequately, but is it really worth paying this much? That's a subjective question, but keep in mind that no one can tell the difference once you've got it on\u2014overpaying doesn't make you look several dollars more chic.", "Given that you don't get any more product than with most eyeshadows, the price is hard to justify, especially considering there are plenty of other eyeshadow quads that perform equally or better for just a nibble of the price. Still, if the expense doesn't hold you back, this is a decent option."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 855}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/in-the-buff-eyeshadow-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "In The Buff Eyeshadow Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Mally Beauty", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "50.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/23B2E08A-A504-4088-97FA-60D548F9E95C_MallyInTheBuffPalette.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Here's another neutral eyeshadow palette, and we must say it's a worthy addition to the growing number of nude palettes out there!", "In The Buff Eyeshadow Palette contains 11 shades, ranging from bone white to neutral taupe to chocolate brown. The shades come in a variety of finishes, some matte, some satin, and some shimmer. The set also includes a creamy, beige \"base\" to put on your lids before you apply the shadows. While the base isn't a necessary step, it does serve its intended purpose\u2014to make the shadows wear longer.", "Each shadow has a smooth texture and is easy to pick up on the double-ended brush included in the palette (though the smaller brush side is better for precision application and blending than the bigger, fluffier side). The shades apply easily, deposit good color, and blend well. They also wear well throughout the day without fading.", "The only issue is that some of the shimmer shades have a fallout issue, meaning they flake onto the face as you apply it, which is not where you want eyeshadow to end up. It's something to consider, especially when you take into account this palette's price.", "Otherwise, if you're interested in this take on nude shadows, we recommend checking it out!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 856}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/colour-riche-dual-effects-eyeshadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Colour Riche Dual Effects Eyeshadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "L'Oreal Paris", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "9.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/519EC0C2-8E31-48D9-873F-A0A9D42EECAC_Loreal_DualEffectsEyeshadow.jpg?w=281", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Colour Riche Dual Effects compacts come with four shades of powder eyeshadow said to \"infuse rich color pigments and saturated pearls with ultra-blendable application\".", "We agree these shadows are easy to blend and offer a shimmering finish, but labeling them richly pigmented is a stretch of the imagination. The pressed powder texture has a tendency to flake during the application process and goes on with less intensity than displayed in the compact (it's on the sheer end of the spectrum).", "There are several combinations of colors, most of which complement each other, including tones of blue, brown, nude, gray, purple, and pink. They all shine with shimmer, and some contain glitter for added sparkle, so if matte shadows are what you want, you'll need to keep shopping.", "If these fragrance-free shadows had better pigmentation, they'd earn a higher rating but as is, they're not really worth a bat of the eye."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 857}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/shadow-play-eyeshadow-quad/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Shadow Play Eyeshadow Quad", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Flower Beauty", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "9.98", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/21C25105-0139-475E-BEE8-89EAD44B5802_FlowerShadowPlayEyeshadowQuad.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["These eyeshadow quads are Flower Beauty's sole powder shadow option \u2013 there are no single- powder shadows yet in this line - though we are happy to report that they are a good option, and a great deal to boot!", "Each quad includes four complementary shadow shades designed to create a coordinated eye design. Three of the shades have subtle shimmer, while the fourth in each set is a matte shade. The texture of each is buttery smooth, and these apply and blend exceptionally well. There is a double-ended sponge-tip applicator included in each compact, but it's not that great; we recommend ignoring it and using a shadow brush instead.", "These shadows don't crease throughout the day, and they don't flake or migrate to other areas of your face. The only downside is that the colors begin to fade about five hours into their wear time. Otherwise, they are great shadows, and for $10, a beauty bargain!", "Shadow Play comes in a good range of colors (we particularly liked the Foxy Browns quad), but those who would rather not contend with green or blue shadows should steer clear of the Secret Garden and Blue Lagoon options."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 858}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/style-eye-con-no-7-plush-shadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Style Eye-Con No. 7 Plush Shadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Marc Jacobs Beauty", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "59.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/CBED3B0D-380D-47E1-B774-78E0B6844147_MarcJacobsStyleEyeConNo7PlushShadow.jpg?w=450", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Style Eye-Con No. 7 palettes are made up of seven pressed powder eyeshadows in varying color families. Each palette contains an assortment of finishes: matte, shimmer, metallic, and glitter.", "In general, the shimmer/metallic shades tend to adhere well to skin, blend on smoothly and wear well throughout the day. The matte shades are a bit on the powdery so can sometimes sheer out upon application so you may have to layer them (the deeper shades have better pigmentation on skin). The matte shades do blend well and also wear well throughout the day, being resistant to creasing, flaking, and fading.", "The shades with overt glitter in them are the duds of the bunch. They don't blend on as smoothly and end up flaking (which is typical of glitter shadows in general). There's only one (at most) in each palette, but still that's a waste when you calculate the price per shade (about $8.50, if you were wondering).", "As far as the color combos go, it's hit or miss. The Lolita palette is the most universally flattering, made up of cream, nude, brown, and pink hues. The other palettes contain playful combinations of shades so it's really up to your preference, but out of those, Siren has  the most unconventional color scheme \u2013 which works is avant-garde is your thing. Neither the Starlet nor the Siren palettes include a matte option.", "For the most part, these palettes perform adequately. It's just a matter of whether or not you can find one that contains a combination of colors that suit you, and you're willing to pay the price to get the designer name."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 859}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/monarch-eyeshadow-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Monarch Eyeshadow Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Kat Von D", "ingredient": "All Shades Contain: Mica,  Silica,  Lauroyl Lysine,  Dimethicone,  Squalane,  Zinc Stearate,  Glyceryl Caprylate,  Hydrogenated Lecithin,  Carthamus Tinctorius (Safflower) Seed Oil,  Rosa Canina Flower Extract,  Trimyristin,  Phenoxyethanol,  Potassium Sorbate. May Contain: Triethoxycaprylylsilane,  Synthetic Fluorphlogopite,  Carmine (CI 75470),  Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891),  Iron Oxides (CI 77491,  CI 77492,  CI 77499),  Tin Oxide (CI 77861).", "size": "", "price": "46.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/AAF4AC4B-C279-449C-A612-687B07141CDD_kat_von_d_monarch_eyeshadow_palette.jpg?w=1000", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["Kat Von D claims this eyeshadow palette was inspired by the colorful wings of a monarch butterfly, and we have to say both the butterfly and this palette are things of natural beauty!", "This large palette contains 12 different shadows, packaged in an interesting way: at the top are three neutral \"base\" shades which are larger than the rest; underneath each base shade are three brighter \"accent\" shades. The idea is that the palette contains three pre-built eye designs you can use (one for each base shade and its three accent shades), though you certainly can mix and match (and we did!). The texture, like those of all Kat von D's eyeshadow palettes, is buttery smooth and creamy, and the finishes include a mix of matte, pearl, and shimmer options. The color quality is good, and the shadows are all easy to blend. They wear well for several hours without creasing or fading, and the colors are very pretty and work well in a variety of combinations. (We were especially surprised by Wrath, a shade which looks bright orange in the pan, but goes on as an attractive burnt copper color.)", "One thing to note: the shimmery gold color included, called \"Summerfly,\" can have some fallout as the day wears on. You can fix this by using primer underneath, or applying it wet, but it's something to keep in mind. Otherwise, this is another winner from a brand that knows its palettes!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 860}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/nude-tude-eyeshadow-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "NUDE \u2018tude Eyeshadow Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "TheBalm", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "36.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/DE230E4F-3774-405C-9E75-5CC900C88AC9_TheBalmNudeTude.jpg?w=1024", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["This nude shadow palette is so beautiful in the pan that we hate to give it just an AVERAGE rating, but in this case, looks aren't everything!", "Nude 'tude comes - like most of theBalm's makeup - in a cute, retro-style cardboard container (you can even choose \"Naughty\" or \"Nice\" artwork on their website). Inside are 12 mostly neutral shadows in shades like soft pink, silvery white, chocolate brown, and shimmering beige. There are varying finishes, including shimmer shades, matte shades, and a couple of glitter shades.", "The color quality of all the shades is good because they have quite a bit of pigment, and they wear well for most of the day without fading.", "Like most of theBalm's powder products, the texture is buttery and smooth, but also powdery, which means you will get a bit of a \"dusty\" powder cloud when you swipe your brush across the shadows and apply them to your lids. With some of the shades this isn't too much of an issue, but it is a problem with the glitter and shimmer shades. In both cases, there is quite a bit of fallout, so much so that it coats your top lashes in shadow, which can quickly lead to eye irritation from the shadow getting into the eye itself.", "We also noticed throughout the day that there was glitter and shimmer on our cheekbones, the bridge of our nose, and on our lower lashes, too! While the colors of this palette are indeed pretty, our \"attitude\" is that you shouldn't have to put up with shadows that fall onto your face and into your eyes, either during application or as the day goes by."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 861}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/shadylady-eyeshadow-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "ShadyLady Eyeshadow Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "TheBalm", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "39.50", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/46EDE9E5-D2D9-44DF-8725-A09A88BC8D97_TheBalmShadyLady.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["\"ShadyLady\" is the name given to three different eyeshadow palettes from theBalm, each containing nine shadows, with shades named after \"Shady Ladies\" (such as \"Mischievous Marissa\" and \"Jet-Setting Jennifer\"). Confusingly, there's some shade overlap, with some colors appearing in more than one palette. These colors that re-appear are mostly neutral shades that can be used with a variety of eye designs.", "Each palette contains only shimmer finish shades, but the shine isn't overpowering; it's just enough to highlight the eye area. Most of the shades are workable, but the ShadyLady Volume 1 palette has a couple of brighter jewel-tone colors (such as emerald green) that we suspect many won't want to use, at least not daily.", "As with most powder products from theBalm, the texture of these shadows is buttery-smooth and easy to pick up on your brush, but it's also a bit powdery, meaning a little dust cloud is part of the deal. Once applied, these shadows blend well and last throughout the day without fading or creasing.", "This is definitely a worthy palette, just be careful with the application so you don't wind up with shadow dust on your clothes!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 862}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/meet-matte-nude-eyeshadow-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Meet Matt(e) NUDE Eyeshadow Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "TheBalm", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "42.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/882F176A-B6C8-4A76-B387-78F60D549F4A_TheBalmMeetMatteNude.jpg?w=860", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["An eyeshadow palette filled with nude matte shades can be a real asset to your makeup stash, and this one is a good option that missed our top rating due to an issue that's endemic to most of theBalm's eyeshadows: a texture that's a bit too powdery.", "Housed in a cardboard compact are nine neutral powder shadows in varying shades of gray, brown, and beige. Each has the name of a different \"Matt\" (Matt Johnson, Matt Malloy, Matt Singh, etc.). Not exactly helpful, but it carries through the play-on-words theme of \"matte\" and \"Matt,\"a joke that gets stale after about 10 seconds.", "The shadows have a buttery texture that's very easy to pick up on your brush, but they are a bit powdery, so take care not to swipe your brush across them too aggressively or it might get messy. They apply smoothly with good color payoff and great blendability. The shades are broad enough that it can work well on many skin tones.", "These are truly matte - no shine to be found here! - and they wear well throughout the day without creasing or fading. If only the texture weren't quite so powdery, this would rank among our favorite palettes."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 863}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/balm-jovi-face-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Balm Jovi Face Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "TheBalm", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "39.50", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/25B9C2F1-9833-49D3-AFAC-C1CC0CBAD477_51NXSN7guhL.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Balm Jovi Face Palette is a strange cosmetic for what seems to be paying homage to the band Bon Jovi, and the two included lip creams - named Milly and Vanilly - only add to the quirkiness of the name. This tries to be all sorts of things at once; unfortunately, it's not quite able to pull all of them off very well!", "This palette definitely offers a lot: There are nine pressed-powder eyeshadows, a powder blush, a powder highlighter, and two lip and cheek creams.", "The eyeshadows include matte, shimmer, and glitter shades, and the colors are mostly workable (white-silver, matte cream, shimmering soft pink, and dark mossy green). They are well pigmented, and they blend and wear well, but most of them are very powdery. Even a soft swipe of your brush across the surface leads to powder going all over the palette. This also leads to some fallout when you apply them.", "The highlighter is a shimmery gold that looks, in the package, like it might not work on most skin tones, but it applies sheer enough that it isn't overpowering - it's just a nice illuminator that doesn't emphasize pores or wrinkles. The peachy pink blush goes on with amazing color - you really need very little of it - and it wears well throughout the day. Regrettably, it's also plagued with the same powdery/flaky texture the eyeshadows have.", "The lip and cheek creams work much better on cheeks than on lips (where they wear off in about two hours), but their performance is average at best (and the creamy, almost greasy, texture means they're not for those with oily skin). All in all, this palette is more opening act than main event - and, unlike Bon Jovi's classic 80's album Slippery When Wet, definitely not a must-have!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 864}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/full-exposure-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Full Exposure Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Smashbox", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "49.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/2A591700-7B7A-42AD-B711-EC34C446BCD8_51F0nGLlinL.jpg?w=450", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Smashbox's Full Exposure Palette can be described as a \"Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde\" type of product, in that it has some aspects that are good \u2013 but others that are just plain bad!", "This shadow palette contains 14 neutral shades. The top row of seven shadows includes a mix of shimmer or glitter shades, while the bottom row is all mattes. This does lend a great deal of versatility to the palette.", "The matte shades are truly matte, and have a soft texture that's easy to apply and blend. The color quality is sheer, meaning you have to put on a couple of layers before it really shows up, but it is buildable and wears well.", "The big problem, though, is in the glitter shades. All of them are quite sheer, and even piling them on to your lids, what comes through more is the glitter \u2013 not the color. With the darker glitter shades, there's also the issue of fallout. If you apply enough to get a full color impact, you will wind up with glitter and shadow on the top of your cheekbones, which is not where eyeshadow is intended to go!", "This is certainly not the worst palette out there, but there are definitely many alternatives that feature a full range of shades that are wearable and don't have the issue with flaking this one does!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 865}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/naked-basics-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Naked Basics Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Urban Decay", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "29.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/DD3896BE-37BB-466A-82B4-8F17C11D4EEF_URBAN-DECAY-2014.png?w=201", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["Consider this a beginner's entry into the Urban Decay family of Naked eyeshadow palettes - a stripped-down offering of six instead of twelve shadows in neutral, mostly -matte shades, save for one shimmery highlighting color.", "The Naked Basics shades are good, but surprisingly limited. Three are in the light beige and cream-colored category, and three are medium to dark browns, so there's a lack of \"in-between\" tan shades that would provide a better gradation from really light and soft to dark eye design. Still, all the colors can be combined for a wide variety of attractive neutral eye looks.", "The pigment quality of all the shades is strong, and you don't have to use much to get a good dose of color. These shadows blend easily and wear well throughout the day, without any obvious fading or creasing.", "What keeps this palette from getting our \"BEST\" rating is its texture. The shadows do apply easily, but they're more powdery than buttery in consistency, which means if you try to pack on too much product you will get fallout on your cheekbones, which is especially unattractive with the darker shades! Otherwise, if you don't mind the lack of medium shades, this is one of the better Naked palettes from Urban Decay."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 866}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/the-natural-shadow-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "The Natural Shadow Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "NYX Cosmetics", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "7.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/F2EDCCD7-BA67-4B11-9145-F9E82FBAE3C9_NYXNaturalShadowPalette.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "1", "expert_reviews": ["NYX's The Natural Shadow Palette looks beautiful in its packaging, but its beauty doesn't translate to beautiful eye designs. This attractive collection of six neutral shadows in three different finishes (shimmer, matte, and satin) seems like a great idea, but in this case, trying to look natural just isn't going to happen!", "Once you swipe your brush across any of the colors, you'll see the problems present themselves\u2014these shadows are powdery to the point of being chalky. Color quality is very poor, meaning these barely show up on your skin even after multiple swipes with your brush. The powdery quality, combined with the skimpy pigmentation, means that you have to pack on these shadows to get any impact\u2014and then, half the shadow winds up falling onto your face.", "Sad to say, but this is a beauty bust, regardless of the nice price! What a shame, too, as NYX's eyeshadows are typically first-rate and rank high on our list of best buys."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 867}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-color-quad/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Eye Color Quad", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Tom Ford", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "82.00", "claims": "Tom Ford eyeshadow quad features four complementary shades that give you a range of looks from bold to smoky, or sexy to subtle. Each features four different finishes too, from a sheer sparkle to a satin to a shimmer to a matte so you can wear each alone or mix and match for an unforgettable look.", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/F45735B5-2CD2-4674-A0E9-194761094CC7_TomFordEyeColorQuad.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Eye Color Quad is a decent group of shadows, though certainly not the best available. Each of the quads available includes a matte, satin, shimmer, and sparkle shade. That's either a plus or a minus depending on what you think of the colors and how much shine you may or may not want from each.", "These shadows do look beautiful, and for the most part are smooth enough that they apply well without any excess shadow falling onto cheeks. The tricky part is the sparkle shade that's included in each compact - they're gorgeous once applied, but you really have to work to get it on without making a mess or having it go where you don't want it. The makeup artist we spoke with recommended not using a brush at all (as it tends to flake with this technique), but instead patting it on gently with a fingertip. This technique works well, but requires a bit more time than if you could just swipe it on with a brush.", "These shadows' color impact is good, and they wear very well with only minimal fading throughout the day. There are some beautiful combinations, which can work for a subtle daytime look or for a more dramatic nighttime look. Most of the quads have colors that are well-coordinated, although the all-blue Cobalt Rush, all-purple Crushed Amethyst, and pink and amber Burnished Amber quads are ones to watch out for. Golden Mink, Cocoa Mirage, and Silvered Topaz, however, are gorgeous!", "Overall, these are good quads, but they're absolutely not the best you can buy - especially considering the price! If you're in the market for designer powder eyeshadow sets, Dior's eyeshadows still reign supreme."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 868}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/naked2-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Naked2 Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Urban Decay", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "54.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/DD3896BE-37BB-466A-82B4-8F17C11D4EEF_URBAN-DECAY-2014.png?w=201", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["These days it seems every blockbuster has to have a sequel, and that's the case with Urban Decay's Naked2 Eyeshadow Palette. The original Naked palette was a runaway hit with a cult following, and rated a Beautypedia \"BEST,\" but does its follow-up live up to the hype? The answer is yes\u2014but Naked2 doesn't quite scale the same peaks as its predecessor.", "Naked2 offers 12 shadows in varying shades of brown, with most in the neutral taupe range. Two of the colors, Foxy and Tease, come in a matte finish; the rest have varying degrees of shimmer, with the Chopper shade having strong glitter. All have a remarkably buttery texture that's a breeze to pick up on a brush and apply.", "The color quality is strong, and wears well throughout the day without fading. All of the shades, regardless of texture, are attractive and can be combined for several different neutral eye looks.", "The only drawback is that the softness of the shadows means they can fall onto your cheekbones while you're packing on the color. It's easily brushed off, but something you should keep in mind. In the case of Chopper, the micro glitter also falls onto your face, which means you'll have sparkles where you probably don't want them!", "Other than that, this is a beautiful palette and a beauty bargain, too. The price breaks down to about $4 a shadow!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 869}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/naked3-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Naked3 Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Urban Decay", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "54.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/DD3896BE-37BB-466A-82B4-8F17C11D4EEF_URBAN-DECAY-2014.png?w=201", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Urban Decay's has two blockbuster beauty products with its Naked and Naked2 eyeshadow palettes, and in true Hollywood fashion, decided to make its collection a trilogy. Naked3 hit the scene with all the fanfare of a big-budget movie premiere, but ultimately it's a disappointment compared to its predecessors.", "Housed in a rose gold-colored tin case, Naked3 features 12 pink-based neutrals. They range in color from the almost-white \"Strange\" to the aptly-named \"Blackheart\" (a deep burgundy with red micro-glitter), with some beautiful copper, mauve, gray, and dusty rose shades in between. The shadows come in a variety of finishes which include matte, satin, shimmer, and glitter, and are, like all eyeshadow palettes, designed to be used together to create a variety of looks.", "Once the pretty packaging is stripped away, what you're left with is a group of shadows that, while gorgeous, are problematic. Each of the shades is almost too creamy yet so sheer that you have to pack on quite a bit to see any substantial color, despite Urban Decay's claim on its site that these shadows contain a special \"Pigment Infusion System\" that imparts rich color.", "The shadows do indeed look good (and wear well) once you've gotten down the application, but you shouldn't have to pile on so much shadow to get a full color effect!", "Another problem is that the glitter shades flake like crazy, meaning you wind up with glitter all over your lashes and your cheeks. This can be mitigated somewhat by applying these shadows wet, but there's still a bit of flaking even with that method.", "Note that the powder eyeshadow formula for Naked3 is different than Urban Decay's other 12-shade Naked palettes, and it's not a change for the better.", "Naked3 certainly isn't a complete bust, but you would be much better off checking out one of the palettes feature on our list of Best Eyeshadows."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 870}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/complete-eye-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Complete Eye Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Burberry Beauty", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "59.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/504ACE4D-C22F-414D-A48C-449586A2F357_Burberry-Logo-2.jpg?w=350", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["In the case of this eyeshadow quad, our \"GOOD\" rating is good, but this certainly isn't a best, and given the price, it should be! Yes, the packaging is gorgeous, but you're not wearing the container; it's only the product inside that matters. The problem with these eyeshadow quads from Burberry is that the quality of the eyeshadows varies with the texture.", "Burberry claims that each eyeshadow is \"customised to give a targeted texture for a specific use: luminising base highlighter, two medium colours to add shape, and an intense liner.\" However, Burberry would have done better to leave well enough alone and just create one outstanding powder shadow texture that works to shape, shade, and define the eye.", "Generally, the medium colors apply evenly and wear well, but the \"intense liner\" shades with deeper pigment\u2014black, chocolate brown, purple\u2014have chalky textures and an inconsistent color deposit, while the \"luminising base highlighter\" fades quickly.", "We always recommend trying products on before buying them, but the quality of these shadows is so spotty that it isn't really worth the time or effort."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 871}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-shadow-eye-couture-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Eye Shadow Eye Couture Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Sonia Kashuk", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "19.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/A64263AD-FDFB-4896-9A52-91F41CF07BD1_SoniaKashukEyeCouture.jpg?w=372", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["This pressed powder eyeshadow palette is slightly larger (and about half as thin) as a standard deck of cards. You get 12 small squares of colors, all of which are well-coordinated and, in this particular palette, truly matte! From nude colors perfect for all-over use to a collection of warm taupe and brown shades for crease color and colors dark enough to use as powder eyeliner, this palette is quite versatile!", "It missed our top rating because the texture, while very smooth and easy to blend, is also drier than usual. This lends a flatter, more drab appearance to each color, so unless you have wrinkled eyelids you'll likely want to add another shadow with a touch of shimmer! Still, applied with good eyeshadow brushes, the shadows in this palette go on easily, have a moderate color payoff that builds well, and the colors resist fading or creasing.", "All in all, there's a lot to like here, and the price makes this palette a beauty bargain, especially for those who like creating a variety of eyeshadow designs."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 872}
