{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/individual-eyes-custom-compact/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Individual Eyes Custom Compact", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "NYC New York Color", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "4.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/7E3D3B2F-44E2-4D8E-B189-7CD004EB3C7A_NYC_CustomCompactSquare.jpg?w=232", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["This six-product eye palette contains a nude eyelid primer, white pearlescent brow bone highlighter, and four shades of powder eyeshadow whose finishes range from matte to frosts. For the price, this is a veritable steal because most of this kit performs very well. The shadows\u2019 color payoff is impressive, and the shades\u2014meant to coordinate with eye color, which is advice best ignored\u2014work well together to create a variety of eye-makeup designs. The sleeper hit here is the eyelid primer, which comes in a generously sized pan. It really does enhance and enrich the shadows, as well as extend their staying power. The only miss is the garish highlighter, which is too iridescent to create a sophisticated highlighting effect."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 901}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eyestudio-by-maybelline-color-plush-silk-eyeshadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Eyestudio by Maybelline Color Plush Silk Eyeshadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Maybelline New York", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "9.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/AC2FC203-3BBE-4077-8205-35280D673AF1_MaybellineEyestudioColorPlushSilk.jpg?w=1024", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["This quad eyeshadow set from Maybelline comes in what may be the cheapest, flimsiest plastic packaging around. Given the professional angle Maybelline is going for with their Eyestudio collection, it\u2019s really surprising they went so cheap on the packaging. It\u2019s almost like what you\u2019d see in a kid\u2019s play makeup set sold at a toy store. The shadow itself is very good, if you don\u2019t mind intense shimmer coupled with large flecks of sparkles that tend to flake. Application is smooth and pigmentation impressive, at least for the darker shades. Most of the color combinations are workable, but avoid Sapphire Siren, Spirited Seas, and Irresistibly Ivy\u2014all are too blue or green."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 902}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/color-design-sensational-effects-eye-shadow-quad-smooth-hold/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Color Design Sensational Effects Eye Shadow Quad Smooth Hold", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Lancome", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "43.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/62D1D55C-E1B3-4142-9D97-D9FF1042FF2A_lancomelogo.gif?w=149", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Although this is an expensive way to assemble an eyeshadow collection, every quad has well-coordinated colors that apply smoothly, if a bit soft, and have a suede-smooth texture. At first glance, some of the quads appear contrasting, but the colors blend together well, with most imparting a soft shimmer finish. The effect of any of the quads isn\u2019t necessarily sensational, but definitely versatile, and the shine doesn\u2019t flake."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 903}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/color-design-eye-brightening-all-in-one-5-shadow-liner-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Color Design Eye Brightening All-in-One 5 Shadow & Liner Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Lancome", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "50.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/E188C90E-21B8-4090-A80D-8F8461F1B792_LancomeColorDesignEyeBrighteningPalette.jpg?w=450", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["This powder eyeshadow palette includes four eyeshadows and a powder line in one sleek compact. You should toss out the sponge-tip applicators Lancome includes because they are poor substitutes for professional eyeshadow brushes. Designed to be applied wet or dry, the shadows have a smooth, almost creamy texture and even application. Applied dry, color impact is surprisingly soft; used wet, the colors go on true and allow for dramatic shading (or pops of bright color, if that\u2019s what you\u2019re after).", "The liner shade in each set is the darkest color and is best used wet for maximum effect. The downside is that all of the palettes have moderate to intense shine; the shiniest shades (those with visible flecks of finely milled glitter) tend to flake."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 904}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/studio-secrets-professional-color-smokes-eye-shadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Studio Secrets Professional Color Smokes Eye Shadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "L'Oreal Paris", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "5.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/2887FE2F-7745-40D3-85DF-D3FD0CBE0D77_LOrealStudioSecretsColorSmokes.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Typically, shimmery powder eyeshadows crease throughout the day, causing eyes to look tired and older. That is not the case with these eyeshadow quads. These pressed-powder eyeshadows have a silky texture, exceptional blendability, and impressively deep pigments, which means you don\u2019t need a lot of shadow to create a gorgeous eye design, and using less helps to prevent creasing. Depending on your taste, you may find that the shades lean too much toward shimmer because each and every shade does have some degree of glint\u2014ranging from a soft frost to flecks of glitter, and, unfortunately, the larger-flecked shadows did flake a bit. So, if you have wrinkles on your lids, they will be more noticeable.", "The quads are assembled as sets of four coordinating shades to create a smokey look, depending on eye color, but don\u2019t feel limited by those designations. Each palette contains a generous size of at least two workable shades."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 905}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/pure-color-five-color-eyeshadow-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Pure Color Five Color EyeShadow Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Estee Lauder", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "50.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/D88E6D7C-3DD4-4893-B23C-68A2D9205A8D_EsteeLauder_PureColorFiveColor.jpg?w=300", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Although this may seem pricey, the cost isn't as hard to take since you\u2019re getting five shade of powder eyeshadow in one sleek compact\u2014and a handful of the sets are coordinated for a beautiful eye design. The enclosed sponge-tip applicators can be tossed because they\u2019re too small and you\u2019ll get much better results from eyeshadow brushes.", "Unlike Lauder\u2019s Pure Color single and duo eyeshadows, those in the Palette have a softer color deposit that must be layered for good intensity (though the darker shades go on quite dark even when applied sheer). The texture is smooth and the formula blends well, which is what you want when you\u2019re applying several shade of eyeshadow.", "Each Palette has at least one matte-finish shade and almost all of them have a color that\u2019s dark enough to use for eyelining. Using each shade in these palettes results in a shiny finish that isn\u2019t\u2019 the best for wrinkled or sagging skin around the eyes.", "More Info:", "Matte eye shadows can work magic that shimmer shadows can\u2019t. Eye shadows with frost, shimmer or flecks of sparkles will always accentuate wrinkled lids and crepey skin because they catch the light, which instantly highlights imperfections. But matte shadows do not reflect light, so they will help camouflage wrinkled lids and fine lines that shimmer shadows exaggerate. Use shimmer shadow to subtly accent your brow bone or to add dimension to dramatic evening looks."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 906}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-transformer/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Eye Transformer", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "e.l.f. Cosmetics", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "3.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/B7924DB3-F88C-4521-AEB0-F619E08503C9_elf_EyeTransformer.jpg?w=300", "expert_rating": "1", "expert_reviews": ["Eye Transformer is nothing more than a quad set of pastel-tinged shiny eyeshadows. Each has a dry texture that flakes during application and none of the shades are that attractive whether worn alone, mixed together, or applied to \"transform\" other shades of eyeshadow. No matter how you slice it, this isn't a transformation for the better!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 907}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/brightening-eye-color/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Brightening Eye Color", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "e.l.f. Cosmetics", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "1.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/943DE903-D1A5-4451-86E4-4758530AFCFB_elf_BrighteningEyeColor.jpg?w=300", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Brightening Eye Color presents a selection of eyeshadow quads packaged with sponge-tip applicators, which should be tossed out. These quads are an amazing value for the money, especially if you prefer sheer colors and don\u2019t mind shine (every quad has some amount of shine, but none are outright glittery). They have a reasonably smooth texture and apply evenly, and every set has at least one shade that can serve as powder eyeliner. The best sets include Matte Mauve (it\u2019s almost matte), Butternut, Drama, and Nouveau (the olive-green shade in this one goes on khaki and blends well with the other colors). You can find eyeshadows that last longer and have a texture that\u2019s more elegant, but you\u2019ll pay a lot more for the privilege."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 908}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/bareminerals-ready-eyeshadow/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "bareMinerals READY Eyeshadow", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Bare Minerals (Bare Escentuals)", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "20.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/773BF16D-FC22-4AD7-AB62-BC6F14050804_BareMineralsReadyShadow.jpg?w=350", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Pressed-powder eyeshadow is a first for bareMinerals, and we\u2019re probably not the only ones wondering what took them so long, given their long-term claims of their loose powder formulas being the only way to go!", "This new version has a silky powder texture that blends on easily and doesn\u2019t have any of the problems of loose-powder eyeshadows. These come in a bevy of shimmer and matte-finish shades. The shadows are sold in sets of 2, 4, or 8, and these groupings explain the step-up in pricing for each, with the duos costing $20, and so on. While not all of the color combinations go well together, there are some attractive shades to consider for either classic or trendy eye designs."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 909}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eyeshadow-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Eyeshadow Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Dr. Hauschka", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "44.95", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/8BBA09E2-B392-4192-A2FC-228F4B002E17_DrHauschkaEyeshadowPalette.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "1", "expert_reviews": ["This talc-based set of four powder eyeshadows comes in a selection of neutral shades that are workable for most fair to medium skin tones. The texture is impressively smooth and application is sheer and even. The darker shades layer well for enhanced coverage and depth. Best of all, the finish is matte!", "The dual-sided sponge-tip applicator should be discarded, but this is a very good option if the shades appeal to you.", "As much as we like these shadows, the price is absurdly high for what you get. For far less money, consider the matte-finish quad eyeshadows from Physicians Formula before this. As for the formula, it\u2019s a shame Dr. Hauschka added fragrance chemicals (citral, geraniol, eugenol) known to be irritating. For this reason, despite its impressive attributes, Eyeshadow Palette is not recommended; in fact, it stands a good chance of causing allergic contact dermatitis around the eyes!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 910}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-quartet-mineral-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Eye Quartet Mineral Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Clarins", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "42.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/356DE672-3975-4FC4-82E6-B0FE0257AC67_41Z2qP9b4HL.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "1", "expert_reviews": ["This powder eyeshadow is sold in sets of four (hence the \u201cquartet\u201d part of the name) and offers some attractive groupings of color, including Nudes, Rosewood, and Graphite. But what\u2019s pretty in the compact doesn\u2019t translate to an eyeshadow we can recommend\u2014especially at this price! Each shade has a dry, almost grainy texture that applies unevenly and unusually soft (it takes several attempts to build much intensity for shaping and shading). ", "Regardless of the palette you choose, every shade has some amount of shine, and many feature obvious sparkles that quickly emphasize wrinkles or a less-than-taut eyelid or drooping brow. All told, this isn\u2019t worth the expense and is a rare makeup disappointment from Clarins."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 911}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/5-couleurs-designer-all-in-one-artistry-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "5-Couleurs Designer All-in-One Artistry Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Dior", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "59.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/2F0944DD-A3F6-496C-8772-D0236B499442_Dior5CouleursDesignPalette.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Housed in one sleek mirrored compact are five eyeshadows. Four are silicone-based and laced with varying degrees of shine, while the darkest shade is essentially a cream eyeliner with an almost-matte finish and enough depth to work as eyeliner. The shadows have a unique silky, airy texture that\u2019s like an ultra-light powder, and they apply beautifully without flaking. Even better, the color, which goes on soft but builds easily, really lasts and resists creasing. The cream eye liner works great whether you desire a thin or thick line, and it\u2019s creamy glide doesn\u2019t veer toward being greasy or looking smeared. One drawback, especially considering this palette\u2019s price, is that the shadows and liner can dry out quickly (for example, all of the open testers at our Sephora store were dried out and unusable). Also, layering the various shades can result in a muddy look rather than smooth gradations of color possible from powder eyeshadows. If you decide to try this, be sure to keep it tightly closed between uses (you may even want to close it between applying each shade)."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 912}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/colour-quartet-for-eyes/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Colour Quartet for Eyes", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Clarins", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "42.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/CA2F3C1A-505B-4812-9757-A1418218812F_31J4eBYJlsL.jpg?w=225", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["The compact for these eyeshadow quads is gorgeous; too bad the color combinations (most of which are pastel-oriented) aren\u2019t. Each powder eyeshadow in the sets has a smooth, dry texture that deposits color somewhat unevenly and with some minor flaking. Every shade is also shiny, so we\u2019re talking maximum spotlight on less-than-taut or wrinkled eye-area skin. If you\u2019re angling for Clarins eyeshadows, the colors they sell singly are much better."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 913}
