{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/color-eyeshadow-palette/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Color Eyeshadow Palette", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Cargo Cosmetics", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "30.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/2AF93308-5E69-4B48-9156-60897A899C9A_CargoColorEyeshadowPalette.jpg?w=450", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Color is definitely the name of the game for these pressed-powder eyeshadow palettes! From the colorful packaging to the mostly odd mix of shades inside these quad sets, you\u2019re given few choices to successfully shape and shade the eye. The eyeshadows themselves have a fairly smooth, dry texture and unusually sheer application/color deposit. They blend well and the shine in each shade clings well enough. But among the many quads, the only workable ones are Baja, Bermuda, and Shanghai; the others are too colorful or contrasting to make the purchase a safe bet."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 917}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/patina-eyeshadows/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Patina Eyeshadows", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Skinn by Dimitri James", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "22.50", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/78DCDB13-C203-4511-9053-C426E80C78FC_SkinnPatinaShadows.jpg?w=1024", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["The Patina Eyeshadows are nearly identical to the powder eyeshadows in Skinn\u2019s Luxe Premier Eyeshadow Collagen Boost Treatment Shadow Collection. The major differences are slimmer packaging and that you get six eyeshadows instead of eight or twelve. These shadows have a very smooth texture and blend beautifully. The light to medium shades apply softly, while the darker shades are richer and ideal for dramatic shading or for use with a damp brush to line the eyes. Every shade has a slight to moderate amount of shine, but it\u2019s not garish or flaky. This would be a good deal if you\u2019ll use all of the shades. Note that the set labeled The Mattes contains mostly shiny eyeshadows. The most workable set is Fashionistas."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 918}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/blush-blink-compact/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-palette-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-palette-reviews ", "product_names": "Blush & Blink Compact", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Palette", "brand": "Skinn by Dimitri James", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "14.50", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/784B3D41-4426-4BF0-8161-BCD3EE8401E6_skinnheaderjpg.jpg?w=400", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["This well-designed palette provides four well-coordinated powder eyeshadows and one powder blush. Although all have smooth, dry textures, application goes from spotty to sheer. The color payoff is so minimal that nearly everyone will need to pile this on to get a noticeable amount of shading and color. We suppose this is workable for those who want really sheer eye and cheek colors, but others will find this frustrating to work with. At least two of the four eyeshadows in each set have shine, but it\u2019s not overwhelming."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 919}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/shape-tape-12-hour-eye-primer-stick/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Shape Tape 12-Hour Eye Primer Stick", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Tarte Cosmetics", "ingredient": "Isohexadecane, Polyethylene, Isononyl Isononanoate, Isododecane, Polyglyceryl-2 Diisostearate, Disteardimonium Hectorite, VP/Eicosene Copolymer, Butyrospermum Parkii (Shea) Butter, Mica, Synthetic Wax, Tocopherol, Tocopheryl Acetate, Ascorbyl Palmitate, Kaolin, Propylene Carbonate, Squalene, Lauryl PCA, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Citric Acid, Caprylyl Glycol, Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499).", "size": "0.10 fl. oz.", "price": "21.00", "claims": "Just like good shapewear, Tarte's Shape Tape 12-hour Eye Primer Stick makes everything go on smoother & last all day. Multitasks as an eye primer, neutral eyeshadow, correcting tint & soft eye highlight while staying crease-free & cake-free for 12 hours. It contains nourishing shea butter to hydrate & pamper the delicate eye area.\n", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/76E15BA8-8AB1-41DC-9AD7-46B93232D369_tarte-cosmetics-coupon-30-off-any-purchase-46qry70u2e2o4ggc4gok8w0ko.jpg?w=200", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Tarte\u2019s Shape Tape 12-Hour Eye Primer Stick has a creamy-smooth texture that\u2019s easy to apply, and we love that it doesn\u2019t contain any fragrance. Beyond this, it isn\u2019t an eyeshadow primer to get excited about.", "This primer is a chunky pencil that you swivel up from the base, no sharpening required. The stick glides over the eye area, adding a pink-beige color, a touch of shine, and light coverage. Unfortunately, the coverage is short-lived (it dissipates in minutes, so if you have any discoloration on your eyelids, expect to need concealer).", "As for the color of this primer, it works as a neutral if you have light to medium skin, but those with darker skin will find this looks ashen and drab.", "The main problem\u2014and this defeats the purpose of using eyeshadow primer\u2014is that the finish remains moist to the touch. It doesn\u2019t set to a silky matte finish that enhances eyeshadow application and wear. If anything, this primer makes it more difficult to apply eyeshadow (especially powder eyeshadow) smoothly.", "Another issue? Unless you set this primer with powder, expect to see some creasing and, if you have oily eyelids, expect smearing and eyeshadow fading at the end of the day.", "In the end, Shape Tape 12-Hour Eye Primer Stick isn\u2019t a worthwhile replacement for priming the eye area with a smooth, matte finish concealer. But if your preference is for a product labeled eyeshadow primer, you\u2019ll find the best eye primers here."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 920}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/pro-filtr-amplifying-eye-primer/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Pro Filt\u2019r Amplifying Eye Primer", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Fenty Beauty", "ingredient": "Isododecane, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Cyclopentasiloxane, Mica, Talc, Polyethylene, Cyclohexasiloxane, Dextrin Palmitate/Ethylhexanoate, VP/Eicosene Copolymer, Triethylhexanoin, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Silica Silylate, Methicone, Propylene Carbonate, VP/Hexadecene Copolymer, Diisostearyl Malate, Tocopheryl Acetate, Polyglyceryl-2 Triisostearate, Dehydroacetic Acid, Titanium Dioxide (Ci 77891), Iron Oxides (Ci 77491, Ci 77492).", "size": "0.27 fl. oz.", "price": "22.00", "claims": "A weightless, color-boosting eyeshadow primer that smooths lids for better blending and longer, crease-proof wear.\n", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/Fenty-Beauty-Pro-Filtr-Amplifying-Eye-Primer.jpg?w=121", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["Pro Filt'r Amplifying Eye Primer joins a long line of Fenty Beauty success stories, as it not only excels in its mission to prevent eyeshadow from creasing, it also facilitates richer, longer-lasting wear!", "Applied with a doe-foot wand, Pro Filt'r Amplifying Eye Primer has a feather-light, silicone-infused consistency that glides over skin with ease. A little goes a long way, as the \u201cinvisipink\u201d tone sheers out to an imperceptible, stay-put finish.", "Those prone to oily eyelids will appreciate how Pro Filt'r Amplifying Eye Primer locks shadow in place for fade-resistant, crease-free wear. Even if that\u2019s not your issue, the base does a great job of amplifying pigmentation so you get richer color from any eyeshadow. All that, and it\u2019s fragrance free. Nice work, Rihanna and the entire Fenty Beauty team!", "Quick tip: Because this formula does such a good job of \u201cgrabbing\u201d on to shadow and locking it in place, we found it helpful to apply a light layer of our normal face powder over the primer, before applying shadow, for smoother, diffused edges. But depending on the kind of look you\u2019re going for, that may not be necessary."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 921}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/air-patrol-bb-cream-eyelid-primer-broad-spectrum-spf-20/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Air Patrol BB Cream Eyelid Primer Broad Spectrum SPF 20", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Benefit", "ingredient": "Active Ingredients: Octinoxate 5.99%,  Titanium Dioxide 2.19%. Inactive Ingredients: Aqua (Water),  Isododecane,  Glycerin,  PEG-9 Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone,  Polysilicone-11,  Methyl Trimethicone,  Pentylene Glycol,  Silica,  Acrylates/Dimethicone Copolymer,  Glyceryl Undecyl Dimethicone,  Phenoxyethanol,  Albizia Julibrissin Bark Extract,  Dimethicone,  Disteardimonium Hectorite,  Aluminum Hydroxide,  Stearic Acid,  Butylene Glycol,  Sodium Myristoyl Glutamate,  Dipotassium Glycyrrhizate,  Propylene Carbonate,  Butyrospermum Parkii (Shea) Seedcake Extract,  BHT,  Sodium Benzoate,  Siegesbeckia Orientalis Extract. May Contain: CI 77163 (Bismuth Oxycholoride),  CI 77491,  CI 77492 (Iron Oxides),  CI 77891 (Titanium Dioxide).", "size": "0.13 fl. oz.", "price": "29.00", "claims": "Air patrol BB cream eyelid primer with broad-spectrum SPF 20 contains EnviroDefend complex known to help guard your delicate eyelids against sun, smoke and pollutants. It also extends the wear of eyeshadow for long-lasting color that wont crease, fade or smear.", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/E6E87DE1-8304-4D7F-AD0A-3551081088A5_Benefit-AirPatrol-sq.png?w=600", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Air Patrol BB Cream Eyelid Primer Broad Spectrum SPF 20 is an eyeshadow primer that soars above the norm to offer standout results with the benefit of added sun protection, all in an easy-to-use, fragrance-free formula.", "Housed in Benefit's usual mix of clever-yet-cute packaging, Air Patrol's formula is dispensed from a click pen component. It's outfitted with what the brand refers to as a \"CushionCalm\" tip that's \"softer than your pinkie!\" which we found to be true. In fact, the tip, which we suspect is made of flexible silicone, makes application a breeze right from the component and it's easy to keep clean.  You will need to use your fingers or a brush to blend it properly on your lids.", "Although Air Patrol doesn't offer substantial coverage, it nicely evens out skin tone on the eyelid and underbrow area, setting to a soft matte finish that feels light. Applying eyeshadow over this is a pleasure; in fact, we noticed it enhanced blending!", "A good eyeshadow primer should at the very least extend eyeshadow wear, and Air Patrol passes this test with \"flying\" colors! It kept our eyeshadow looking just-applied (and perfectly in place) for well over 12 hours. Your mileage may vary depending on how oily your eyelids are and which type of shadow (creams or powders, powders are usually preferred for long wear) you apply, but we were impressed!", "Also impressive is the reliable broad spectrum sun protection this eyeshadow primer provides. Its blend of synthetic (octinoxate) and mineral (titanium dioxide) sunscreens had us a bit wary, as octinoxate can be sensitizing for some when applied around the eyes. However, we found it to be a non-issue\u2014and we did test on it a staffer whose eye area normally reacts when octinoxate is applied around the eyes.", "Air Patrol only comes in one shade, a sheer, light nude tone with a slight yellow cast. The slightly warm color will work for most skin tones and does a good job neutralizing the pink to bluish-purple some people have on their eyelids. But again, if your eyelid area has more marked discoloration, then you'll want to apply your usual concealer and follow with this eyeshadow primer.", "Benefit claims that their \"EnviroDefend\" complex guards not only against sun exposure but also smoke and pollution in the air. Although the sun protection will happen, we're skeptical that the tiny amounts of antioxidants in the formula can do all that much to shield the eye area from environmental pollutants. Still, their combined presence likely provides some benefit, just not a total shield from pollutants!", "To bring this review in for a landing (somebody stop us!), Air Patrol BB Cream Eyelid Primer Broad Spectrum SPF 20 earns a strong recommendation from us for its easy-to-blend, long-wearing formula, applicator tip, sun protection, and ability to not only enhance eyeshadow application but keep shadow vibrant and in place for an entire workday (and then some!).  Benefit Cosmetics certainly earned their \"stars and stripes\" with this fab product.", "Note: This product was recently downgraded from 5-stars to 4-stars due to its less-than-optimal SPF rating. Although this does provide sun protection, it's less than SPF 30. The problem? Health experts and medical boards around the globe agree that SPF 30 or greater is best when it comes to providing a reliable defense against the damage the sun can do. Yes, a foundation with less than SPF 30 is acceptable if your daytime moisturizer is rated SPF 30 or greater, but we wouldn't want anyone thinking an SPF under 30 is the best for skin. See More Info below for details.", "Sunscreens Rated Lower than an SPF 30: An extensive body of research and a growing number of medical organizations around the world have determined that a sunscreen rated SPF 30 or greater is mandatory to ensure adequate sun protection.", "Although a sunscreen rated lower than 30 will provide protection at the SPF number on the label and may claim broad-spectrum protection, we always point out when it does not have a rating of SPF 30 or greater because that's so important for the health and appearance of your skin.", "References for this information:", "Journal of Clinical Oncology, September 2016, ePublication", "Photodermatology, Photoimmunology, and Photomedicine, August 2014, pages 212\u2013219", "The Journal of Clinical and Aesthetic Dermatology, September 2012, pages 18\u201323", "Journal of the American Academy of Dermatology, May 2008, Supplemental, pages S149\u2013S154", "https://www.aad.org/forms/policies/uploads/ps/ps-broad-spectrum%20protection%20of%20sunscreen%20products.pdf", "http://www.aacr.org/Newsroom/Pages/News-Release-Detail.aspx?ItemID=857#.V9HN45grLcs"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 922}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/extreme-wear-eye-primer/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Extreme Wear Eye Primer", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Sonia Kashuk", "ingredient": "Isododecane,  Hydrogenated Polyisobutene,  Dimethicone,  Squalane,  Ceresin,  Synthetic Wax,  Talc,  Polyglyceryl-2 Diisostearate,  Cetyl Ethylhexanoate,  Silica Silylate,  Silica,  Boron Nitride,  Lauroyl Lysine,  Hydrogenated Styrene/Isoprene Copolymer,  HDI/Trimethylol Hexyllactone Crosspolymer,  Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate,  Plukenetia Volubilis Seed Oil,  Carmine. May Contain: Mica,  Titanium Dioxide,  Iron Oxides,  Ultramarines,  Manganese Violet,  Ferric Ammonium Ferrocyanide,  Chromium Oxide Greens,  Chromium Hydroxide Green,  Blue 1 Lake,  Yellow 5 Lake.", "size": "0.07 fl. oz.", "price": "8.99", "claims": "The silky, weightless formula glides on to smooth the skin, create the perfect canvas for color application and enhance staying power. The lightweight formula contains African Walnut Seed Oil to restore and protect skins elasticity, emollients to smooth the skin and micro-fine pigments for an even flawless finish.", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/F3D5B7FD-492C-4AFA-A933-D1F59C63E193_SoniaKashuk-ExtremeWearPrimer-sq.png?w=500", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Eye makeup can be one of the most fun parts of a beauty routine, but eyeshadows that fade and crease throughout the day can make even the most beautiful shades a pain to wear. Sonia Kashuk's Extreme Wear Eye Primer claims it can eliminate this problem thanks for a formula that ensures shadows stay put where you apply them. Unfortunately, its performance doesn't quite fit the bill, which is why it earned an average rating.", "Extreme Wear Eye Primer comes in a glass pot with a screw-top lid. Inside is a fragrance-free, medium nude-toned paste that warms to a thinner texture if you use your fingers to apply it. The texture still remains somewhat tacky as you put it on, dragging slightly on skin\u2014it doesn't \"glide\" on as Sonia Kashuk describes. We found it's more effective to pat this on to lids rather than spread it over them.", "The texture isn't necessarily a negative, as the slight tackiness helps eyeshadows adhere more readily than if it were overly emollient\u2014but its texture is something to consider if this isn't your preference in primers (and if the smooth factor advertised is a selling point for you). We did find this enhanced the color quality of both cream and powder shadows, making the colors appear bolder upon initial application than if they were applied on their own.", "Extreme Wear Eye Primer also helps shadows last longer in terms of color intensity, extending their wear and delaying any noticeable fading by a couple of hours. Unfortunately, it did not make any difference in preventing or slowing down creasing in eye shadows. We could still see noticeable creasing within a couple of hours following application with powder formulas, and this was even more pronounced with cream eyeshadows that have emollient textures.", "Overall, while Sonia Kashuk's Extreme Wear Eye Primer can help improve both the color quality and delay fading of your eyeshadow, the fact that shadows still crease while it's on means it doesn't rank with the best eye primers on the market, or even in comparison to just using a good concealer as a primer. We recommend instead one of the options on our list of Best Eyeshadow Primers."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 923}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eyeshadow-primer-potion-anti-aging/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Eyeshadow Primer Potion Anti-Aging", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Urban Decay", "ingredient": "Isododecane,  Talc,  Cyclopentasiloxane,  Trimethylsiloxysilicate,  Triethylhexanoin,  Oryza Sativa (Rice/Riz) Bran Oil,  Trihydroxystearin,  Disteardimonium Hectorite,  Polyethylene,  Sorbitan Sesquioleate,  VP/Hexadecene Copolymer,  C12-15 Alkyl Benzoate,  Dimethicone,  Alumina,  Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride,  Phenoxyethanol,  PEG-40 Stearate,  Synthetic Beeswax,  Propylene Carbonate,  Hexyl Laurate,  Polyglyceryl-4 Isostearate,  Tribehenin,  PEG-10 Dimethicone,  Stearic Acid,  Ethylhexylglycerin,  Ceramide 2,  PEG-10 Rapeseed Sterol,  Alaria Esculenta Extract,  Palmitoyl Oligopeptide,  Water. May Contain: Mica,  Titanium Dioxide,  Iron Oxides,  Bismuth Oxychloride.", "size": "0.33 fl. oz.", "price": "24.00", "claims": "A 24-hour wear, creamy eye shadow primer that supports antiaging and ensures that eye shades stay vibrant and crease-free.  Dermaxyl helps to smooth the appearance of wrinkles, and Kalpariane supports plumping, firming, and hydrating the skin as it improves suppleness and elasticity. The optical blurring pigments create a subtle, soft-focus effect that instantly brightens up tired eyes and reduces the look of redness, thinning skin in the eye area, and other imperfections.", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/C91FF16B-60E5-4713-AB6F-3CDEA38CFF60_Urban-Decay-Anti-Aging-Primer-Potion-sq.png?w=600", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["Eyeshadow Primer Potion Anti-Aging works incredibly well as primer for fade-resistant, crease-free eyeshadow, but its anti-aging capabilities are farfetched. It's absolutely worth consideration if you need help keeping your eyeshadow looking fresh all day\u2014just don't count on it to make your wrinkles go away.", "This \"anti-aging primer potion\" differs a bit from the look and feel of Urban Decay's other eyeshadow primer potions, but most closely resembles the original with its creamy silicone consistency that blends effortlessly into skin. Just a dab with the doe foot applicator goes a long way, as the lightly tinted, peachy tone sheers out to an imperceptible finish suitable for any skin color.", "Once you give it a minute to set, the fragrance-free formula dries down to a comfortable matte finish that keeps eyeshadow in place for hours of fade/crease resistant-wear\u2014even for those with oily skin! Just keep in mind that while this primer creates a smooth base for eyeshadow, it also \"grabs\" on to shadow\u2014so to avoid a choppy shadow application, blend swiftly..", "The only thing holding this back from earning our top rating is that it can't deliver on its skincare-esque promises to improve wrinkles, firmness, etc. Urban Decay specifically calls out the trademark ingredients Dermaxyl (A.K.A palmitoyl oligopeptide) and Kalpariane (Alaria Esculenta (brown algae) Extract, both of which have anti-aging properties, but as the second/ third to last ingredients, they are in too little of concentration to make an impact on skin.", "If you're going to buy Eyeshadow Primer Potion Anti-Aging, do it for its power to improve the wear of your eyeshadow\u2014not for its anti-aging claims. Nothing more, nothing less!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 924}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/24-hour-photo-finish-shadow-primer/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "24 Hour Photo Finish Shadow Primer", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Smashbox", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "21.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/7F276E1D-8E52-49C7-99A6-CF0DE9B62570_Smashbox_25HourPhotoFinishShadowPrimer.jpg?w=350", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["Before we say anything about the performance of this eyeshadow primer, a note about the 24 hour claim: don't put this to the test! We don't recommend wearing any makeup for 24 hours, as at some point you're going to need to sleep and sleeping in makeup is bad for your skin, not to mention a leading cause of waking up to puffy, red eyes.", "What sets this fragrance-free primer apart from others is its texture. While most primers (both for shadows and foundations) are gel-like in nature, this one is more of a thick, waxy balm. That might be off-putting initially, but it begins to \"warm up\" once you work it between your fingers and get softer, making it easy to apply to eyelids.", "The primer does go on smoothly, though the texture remains a bit \"sticky\" and waxy until it's had about a minute to dry. Apply your shadow before the primer fully sets and you will have a difficult time blending because the shadow will drag across the somewhat tacky surface. Once this has set, you'll have a much easier time applying your shadow, so don't be too hasty.", "This primer makes the color intensity of the shadow you're wearing stronger, and it will not budge all day long. We tried to get this to move, even rubbing our finger on our eye design, and it didn't waver \u2013 this primer definitely increases shadow wear time with no creasing, fading, or flaking throughout the day.", "Just remember \u2013 let this set! Once you've made it past the learning curve, you're left with a primer that does what it says, and does it very well."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 925}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/extreme-wear-eyeshadow-primer/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Extreme Wear Eyeshadow Primer", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Ulta", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "10.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/46352348-FA84-41E0-9A7B-B1CDE767DC87_imagesCAE3A2VN.jpg?w=225", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["Ulta claims Extreme Wear Eyeshadow Primer will \"make eye shadow last all day and night without creasing or fading,\" and we'd agree!", "The talc-based, fragrance-free formula has a light, peachy-white color that applies so translucently you can hardly detect it, but you will \"see\" the great results when it comes to promoting long eyeshadow wear.", "The primer goes on super smooth and sets to a matte finish that helps eyeshadow stay in place all day. Those with oily skin and/or deep-set eyelids will particularly appreciate its ability to prevent creasing.", "Well done Ulta\u2014and the price makes this a beauty bargain, too!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 926}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/put-a-lid-on-it/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Put A Lid On It", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "TheBalm", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "18.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/6507DAFB-3E88-4B7D-8C0B-181F8BC1AB75_41FL34-Rj9L.jpg?w=277", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["This lightweight eyeshadow primer does a great job of smoothing the eyelid and giving eyeshadow a base to adhere to for increased wear time. In essence, it does what an eyeshadow primer should do!", "The texture of this clear, gel-like primer seems a bit thick when you first squeeze it out of the tube, but after you apply it and it dries (which takes only a few seconds), it feels very light.", "Put A Lid On It does smooth the lid area well, decreasing the chance that shadows will crease or fade during the day. It also makes shades that are somewhat sheer or muted appear to have stronger color, and it's easy to remove at the end of the day."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 927}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/all-about-shadow-primer-for-eyes/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "All About Shadow Primer for Eyes", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Clinique", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "19.50", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/E867371D-61E2-471F-9065-4D49C19CB237_Clinique_AllAboutShadowEyes.jpg?w=300", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Clinique's All About Shadow Primer for Eyes is a beige-tone primer that's packaged with a wand applicator. It goes on satiny-smooth, melding into skin quickly and drying to a silky powder finish. There are four color options available\u2014from very light to very dark\u2014but the finish is so sheer it doesn't really make a difference.", "As for extending the wear time of shadows, this does a good job of making sure eyeshadow stays put (that is, the shadow remains where you applied it instead of migrating to other areas of the face as some shadows do), but it doesn't really make it last much longer than it would without a primer. You can do just as well using your matte-finish foundation or concealer for the same purpose\u2014and save some money, too!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 928}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/intense-i-color-liquid-shadow-color-primer/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Intense i-Color Liquid Shadow + Color Primer", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Almay", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "7.99", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/897FDE15-F5F1-4B59-BB98-3EF81668FA06_Almay_IntenseiColorPrimer.jpg?w=152", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Almay advertises Intense I-Color Liquid Shadow + Color Primer as a revolutionary product, but when it comes right down to it, it's about as revolutionary as white bread! The only thing intense about it is the name.", "This liquid shadow comes with a wand applicator that you're supposed to swipe over the eyelids. The shadow itself is pretty sheer with some subtle shimmer, and it takes a few swipes to get it to really show up.", "Like most Almay Intense I-Color eye products, this comes color-coded for brown, blue, hazel, and green eyes. Although the eyeshadow color you choose can indeed enhance your natural eye color, in this case Almay's colors aren't all that logical. For example, if you have blue eyes you're directed to use the Sky Blue shade, thus putting blue next to blue. The problem? This isn't a case where like enhances like; rather, if you want to enhance your eye color, choose a contrasting or neutral color rather than a matching shade. So, for blue eyes, go for a soft peach or cantaloupe color, or any shade of soft brown\u2014definitely not blue! In the real world of fashion, eye makeup is about shaping the eye with neutral tones, not wearing color. Want proof? Just look at any cover of a fashion magazine.", "The shadow doesn't crease during the day, but fades a bit after a few hours. As a primer for other shadows, the sheerness allows other colors to be put over it without a \"muddy\" looking result, but it doesn't make any significant difference in the amount of wear time for the shadow you put over it. Overall, this is just very average and offers very few to no real benefit."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 929}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eyeshadow-primer-2/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Eyeshadow Primer", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Avon", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "7.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/D7DD2B71-761B-4089-A177-1C7BD6369EB4_AvonEyeshadowPrimer.jpg?w=450", "expert_rating": "3", "expert_reviews": ["Avon's Eyeshadow Primer is a nice addition to their makeup line, though if you're already using a matte finish liquid foundation or concealer to prime your eyelids then you don't need to add a product like this, too. What you get here is a  fleshy peach-tinted cream housed in a tiny glass jar. Applied with a brush, the cream softens at skin temperature and becomes easy to blend over the eyelid area, setting to a powder finish with a slight pink tinge.", "The color of this primer is worth discussion, because it impacts the color of any eyeshadow applied over it. For example, a grayish-plum shadow applied to bare skin goes on color-true but the same shade applied over Avon's primer looks lavender pink. That's not a deal-breaker but is something to keep in mind should you decide to try this primer.  The formula is fragrance-free and contains a high amount of talc, which contributes to the matte finish and relative opacity this has.", "The finish does allow eyeshadows to last longer and helps them resist creasing\u2014but again, so can a good concealer or foundation that set to a matte finish. Eyeshadow primers have their place, but for some they're simply superfluous."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 930}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eyeshadow-primer/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Eyeshadow Primer", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Palladio Beauty", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "8.00", "claims": "Enhanced with 5 different herbal extracts as well as Vitamins A, C and E, this sheer, silicone-based formula glides on like silk and then vanishes instantly. Its the ultimate makeup kit accessory, that eliminates creasing and ensures maximum shadow vibrancy all-day long.", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/0947A0C9-341A-41E9-98DF-9B4DF82119A9_Palladio_EyeShadowPrimer.jpg?w=1024", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["This silky, silicone-based eyeshadow primer enhances the look and wear of eyeshadow, while also treating eyelids to a variety of antioxidants. It applies smoothly and evenly with a sponge-tip wand, but for even better control, use a clean fingertip to blend.", "Palladio Eyeshadow Primer comes in a very light cream shade that sheers out to a nearly translucent, soft shimmer finish that is workable for all skin tones. If using concealer or foundation as an eyeshadow base isn't doing enough to smooth fine lines and enhance eyeshadow application or wear, this primer will definitely do the trick, and it's fragrance-free."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 931}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/high-voltage-skin/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "High Voltage Skin", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Kat Von D", "ingredient": "Water,  Isododecane,  Dimethicone,  Trimethylsiloxysilicate,  Butylene Glycol,  Cetyl PEG/PPG-10/1 Dimethicone,  Polyethylene,  Polysilicone-11,  PEG/PPG-18/18 Dimethicone,  Lecithin,  Boswellia Serrata Gum Extract,  Honey Extract,  Camellia Sinensis Leaf Extract,  Aspalathus Linearis Extract,  Quaternium-90 Bentonite,  Troxerutin,  Hexyl Laurate,  Magnesium Aluminum Silicate,  Polyglyceryl-4 Isostearate,  Triethoxycaprylylsilane,  Sodium Chloride,  C18-36 Acid Triglyceride,  PEG-10 Dimethicone,  Propylene Carbonate,  Stearic Acid,  Cholesterol,  Capryly Glycol,  Alumina,  Silica,  Hexylene Glycol,  Tetrapeptide-14,  Potassium Sorbate,  Sodium Benzoate,  Phenoxyethanol. May Contain (+/-): Mica (CI 77019),  Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891),  Iron Oxides (CI 77491,  CI 77492,  CI 77499).", "size": "0.04 fl. oz.", "price": "15.00", "claims": "This smooth-textured essential glides over the eyelid without dragging. It performs like a magnet, preventing eyeshadow from migrating and creasing. Micro-encapsulated pigments float over the eye area, finessing skin texture and blurring fine lines. Use the Smoky shade to prep your lids for a smoldering smoky-eye look.", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/0F9768B5-E3BF-460C-8350-6DBA8A61B418_kat_von_d_high_voltage_skin.jpg?w=450", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["This fragrance-free eyeshadow primer has a thick, creamy texture that sheers out enough to fully prime eyelids with less than a pea-size amount. It's easy to apply with a clean fingertip, and sets within seconds to a smooth, crease-resistant matte finish.", "Although High Voltage Skin is available in only one shade\u2014\"Skin\"\u2014the good news is that this shade is a neutral beige color. This primer is light enough to work on either pale or dark skin tones to improve the overall wear and vibrancy of any eyeshadow applied over it.", "As for the light dusting of antioxidants in the formula, it's not enough to do much of anything for your skin, but those ingredients will remain stable thanks to being packaged in an opaque tube. Also thanks to the packaging, you don't have to worry about this primer drying out after continued use, which is a risk with similar eyeshadow primers that are housed in jars or compacts!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 932}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-shadow-base/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Eye Shadow Base", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "NYX Cosmetics", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "7.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/6609E226-9ECB-483F-94B1-AB0F7DA7DA16_417IigWEZRL.jpg?w=500", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["Eye Shadow Base is an eyeshadow primer packaged in a small jar. It has a creamy texture that blends down to an almost powdery feel, but still has enough staying power to intensify the color of whatever eyeshadow you put over it. The formula helps eye makeup stay in place and prevents creasing, although those with oily eyelids may still experience some creasing by the end of the day.", "The shades include White, White Pearl (a glittery white), and Skin Tone (warm beige). They each intensify eyeshadows in different ways, but we suggest avoiding the White Pearl shade because the glitter particles are overdone and end up traveling to other areas of your face. All in all, this is an OK eyeshadow base, but we've seen better (including others from NYX)."], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 933}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/stick-around-eye-primer/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Stick Around Eye Primer", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Bare Minerals (Bare Escentuals)", "ingredient": null, "size": "", "price": "20.00", "claims": null, "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/6CDFBE18-5809-4387-90F0-4FC944ADA8CA_BareMineralsBuxomStickAroundEyePrimer.jpg?w=450", "expert_rating": "4", "expert_reviews": ["This eye primer/eyeshadow base comes in retractable stick with a semi-stiff texture. The stiff texture makes it is a little tricky to apply since added pressure is required to achieve an even base, but that \u201cno slip\u201d feel is what makes this product work. It not only intensifies and holds eye makeup in place, but also it offers crease-free lids for several hours.", "The downside is it does such a good job holding makeup in place that it makes it difficult to blend eyeshadow.", "Whether or not you\u2019ll like this product really depends on what you want out of it. If you are looking for crease-free lids at any cost, go for it. But if you want something that makes eyeshadow application easier, this isn\u2019t going to be for you. It comes in a single, nude shade that wears well under other eye makeup and sheers out imperceptibly for all skin tones.", "Pros:", "Cons:"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 934}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/eye-prep-fx-anti-age-smoothing-primer/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "Eye Prep FX Anti-Age Smoothing Primer", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "Cover FX", "ingredient": "Water,  Glycerin,  Diethylhexyl Carbonate,  Squalane,  Acrylates Copolymer,  Cucumis Sativus (Cucumber) Fruit Extract,  Behenyl Alcohol,  Glyceryl Stearate,  Butyrospermum Parkii (Shea Butter),  Palmitic Acid,  Stearic Acid,  Acrylic Acid/VP Crosspolymer,  Phenoxyethanol,  Triethanolamine,  Caprylyl Glycol,  Cetyl Alcohol,  Lauryl Alcohol,  Lecithin,  Myristyl Alcohol,  Steareth-20,  Hesperidin Methyl Chalcone,  PVP/Polycarbamyl Polyglycol Ester,  Hydrolyzed Sesame Protein PG-Propyl Methylsilanediol,  N-Hydroxysuccinamide,  Dipeptide-2,  Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-7,  Chrysin,  Palmitoyl Oligopeptide", "size": "", "price": "43.00", "claims": "This smoothing, silicone-free primer immediately hydrates and reduces undereye puffiness. Formulated to strengthen the skin around the eye, this primer firms and rejuvenates while lightening dark undereye circles. It also doubles as a primer bonding to concealer and eyeshadow for even, color-true, long-lasting wear.", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/FE5C6568-4B33-47C3-B187-D70DCF477BE8_CoverFXEyePrepFXAntiAgingPrimer.jpg?w=200", "expert_rating": "2", "expert_reviews": ["This fragrance-free, eye-area primer contains several ingredients that show up in numerous other products claiming to lighten dark circles and reduce puffiness. Unfortunately, none of those ingredients have research proving they work (and given the number of products that contain those ingredients, you'd think no one would be concerned about dark circles or puffiness because they should all work, but alas, none do).", "Beyond the dark circle and puffiness-reducing claims, this primer has a light, gel-cream texture that doesn't do much to \"prime\" skin around the eyes. It's not a special product to add to your routine, and doesn't contain anything that would help concealer or eye makeup last longer. What you're getting is a lightweight moisturizer for the eye area, one that contains enough film-forming agent to make skin look smoother. That's nice but you can get more benefits from countless serums or moisturizers suitable for use around the eyes (you don't need a special eye cream; see More Info for details). If you opt to try this anyway, it\u2019s best for normal to slightly dry skin.", " Pros:", " Cons:", "More Info:", " We know it\u2019s hard to believe, but the truth is you don\u2019t need a special product for the eye area, whether labeled eye cream or something else. Although there is much you can do to improve the skin around your eyes, the ingredients capable of doing that don't need to come from, and often aren't even included in, an eye cream. For example, most eye creams (such as this one) don't contain sunscreen, and that is a serious problem because it leaves the skin around your eyes vulnerable to sun damage, which will make dark circles and wrinkling worse!", "You can save money and take superior care of your eye area by using your face product, if it is well formulated and appropriate for the skin type around your eyes!"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 935}
{"product_links": "https://www.beautypedia.com/products/hd-eye-shadow-base/?archive_search=%2Fmakeup%2Feyes%2Feyeshadow-primer-reviews%2F%3Fsize%3D96%26makeup_group%5B0%5D%3Deyeshadow-primer-reviews ", "product_names": "HD Eye Shadow Base", "category": "Eye Makeup", "sub_category": "Eyeshadow Primer & Base", "brand": "NYX Cosmetics", "ingredient": "Isododecane,  Talc,  Beeswax,  Dimethicone,  Disteardimonium Hectorite,  Cyclopentasiloxane,  Trimethylsiloxysilicate,  VP / Eicosene Copolymer,  Propylene Carbonate,  Sorbitan Sesquioleate,  Phenoxyethanol,  Phenoxyethanol / Methylparaben,  Ethylparaben / Butylparaben,  Propylparaben / Isobutylparaben,  Colorant,  CI 77891 (Titanium Dioxide),  CI 77492 (Iron Oxide Yellow),  CI 77499 (Iron Oxide Black),  CI 77491 (Iron Oxide Red)", "size": "", "price": "7.00", "claims": "Prep your eyelids with this lightweight eye makeup primer that makes skin appear smoother, more even toned, and ensures lasting makeup application. The High Definition Eye Shadow Base conceals creases and pumps up the vibrancy of your eye shadow.", "image_url": "https://www.beautypedia.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/897B2858-5745-4DDE-9386-37750CC4BFA1_NYXCosmetics_HDEyeShadowBase.jpg?w=53", "expert_rating": "5", "expert_reviews": ["This liquid eyeshadow base sets to a powder-like, matte finish that enhances shadow and liner application. The absorbent formula helps keep oily lids at bay and prevents creasing throughout the day. It applies smoothly and evenly with a sponge-tip wand.", "HD Eye Shadow Base comes in a universal, light peach shade that is so sheer it hardly shows, so this is more about the powdery finish than adding color. It\u2019s definitely worth considering if you find that using concealer or foundation as an eyeshadow base doesn\u2019t do the trick for you.", "Pros:", "Cons:"], "expert_pros": null, "expert_cons": null, "jar_package": null, "animal_test": null, "user_rating": null, "product_id": 936}
